title: buerre blanc sauce
directions: In pan, combine wine, vinegar and onions; reduce to 2 tablespoons over high heat.
Cool slightly, then gradually add butter, whisking until well blended.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve warm with any type of fish.
Serves 6.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown beef with 1/2 cup onion.
Add taco seasoning.
Add to already hot beans.
Cover with onions and cheese.
Heat well. Great over rice.
Great way to use leftover beans.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips, and mix at low speed until thoroughly moistened.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Shape into 1 1/4 balls and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.	Bake 9 to 12 minutes or until top appears cracked.
Makes 32 cookies.
tags: moist supreme butter chocolate cake mix

title: potato salad sauce
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat and add well beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Cook until slightly thickened. Beat in the salad dressing.
Pour over potato salad.

title: zucchini scramble
directions: Heat oil in frying pan. Spread sliced zucchini and onions in frying pan and cover. Let cook, over medium heat, until fork goes easily into zucchini. Break eggs and scramble with zucchini and onion. Add salt and pepper. Serves 2.

title: marion's rye bread
directions: Pour 1 quart boiling water on top.
Mix well.
When cooled to lukewarm (115°), add 1 package dry yeast, dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add white flour (takes quite a bit).
Let rise, make into 4 loaves, prick with a fork and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: yorkshire meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, soup mix, chili sauce and 1 egg in a bowl; mix well.
Shape into small meatballs.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sift flour and baking powder into bowl.
Add mixture of 4 eggs, milk and margarine; beat until blended.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mom's peanut brittle
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until spins good thread.
Add peanuts.
Cook until light golden brown, stirring constantly. Take off stove; stir in vanilla and butter, then add soda.
Stir until fluffy.
Pour out on very lightly buttered cookie sheet; spread thin.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Heat bacon drippings in large skillet (or wok).
Add cabbage and apple.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over cabbage. Cover skillet.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, for 15 to 20 minutes or until cabbage and apples are tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream with mixer or mash bananas to make 1 1/2 cups.
Set aside.
Cream together the butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix together alternately with buttermilk and bananas.
Fold in nuts.
Put into 2 small or 1 large bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: ice cream pumpkin pie
directions: Arrange 19 to 20 gingersnaps over bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Crush remaining gingersnaps.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Line a pie plate with crust, fill with chopped rhubarb. Sprinkle with cinnamon after adding the sugar, flour and cream. Bake at least 3/4 hour if using uncooked rhubarb at 350° or in moderate oven.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in sugar and cinnamon. Combine the next 3 ingredients.
Heat to boil and then dip the biscuits in mixture; put in a greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes; pour the remaining of the first mixture on top before you bake.

title: jiffy jello
directions: Heat applesauce to boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in jello until completely dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries and continue stirring until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into clear glass bowl or square dish.
Refrigerate and let set.
May be decorated with Cool Whip and whole fresh strawberries.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown chops.
Drain on absorbent paper. In a buttered 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes and chops.
In a small bowl, combine water and soup mix.
Pour over meat.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: In
heavy skillet, saute green pepper, onion and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add
chicken
and saute until no longer pink. Add tomatoes
and
seasonings.	Cook
to 30 minutes until chicken is	cooked	through.
Sprinkle
with olives and serve with pasta.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well. Shape into balls and dip in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Mix sugar, water, vinegar and bring to a boil.
Dissolve gelatin in little more than 1/2 cup cold water and add to boiled mixture which has been removed from cooking.
Pour into 2 quart oblong casserole dish to cool.
Can put in refrigerator, but don't allow to congeal.

title: ham and black-eyed peas
directions: Soak peas overnight in water.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients, except rice, in 6 quart pressure cooker.
Secure lid. Cook at 15 pounds of pressure for 35 minutes.
Remove pressure, then remove lid.
Place ham on carving board, trim fat; slice.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage. Remove from heat. Add the peanut butter. Do not stir until cool enough to beat.
Beat until creamy. Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into buttered dish. Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together and pour into chocolate graham cracker crust. Refrigerate 5 hours.
Before serving, garnish with chocolate shavings, if desired.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine butter, flour, eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in crabmeat, cheese and onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: pecan praline
directions: Mix all sugars, salt and Pet milk, then cook.
When it comes to a boil, add pecans and stir until it comes to a boil again. When it forms a soft ball when dropped in a cup of cold water, remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: sweet-sour swiss chard
directions: Tear small pieces chard or spinach.
Set aside.
Cook bacon crisp.
Save liquid.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Use grease. Cook green onion until tender.
Add sugar, flour and salt, stir in water and vinegar.
Cook and stir until thick.
Pour over salad. Add bacon, red onion, fresh mushrooms, eggs and Cheddar, Jack or Swiss cheese, grated finely.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix the dressing and margarine; put half the mix on bottom of pan.
Add sour cream, soup, onion and zucchini.
Put rest of dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix Crisco, flour, salt and baking powder.
Chop with pastry blender until it resembles cornmeal.
Then add milk, a little at a time, using fork, working lightly with a little flour and roll out. Makes 2 - 9 inch crusts.

title: fried squash cakes
directions: Grate raw squash and onions and mix with remaining ingredients, except the oil.
Heat the oil in frying pan and drop mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into oil, turning when cakes reach desired brownness.

title: cocoa cookies
directions: Shape into 1 inch balls and dip in beaten egg whites and then sugar.
Bake on greased pans at 350 for 15 minutes.
This makes a lot, it's okay to cut in half.

title: mother's millionaires
directions: Combine caramels and milk in microwave-safe dish.
Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes or until melted.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Dip in melted almond bark.
Let stand on waxed paper until set.
Yield: 42 servings.

title: easy brittle
directions: Line sheet cake pan with foil. Cover with graham crackers. Spread pecans on crackers. Boil butter, margarine and sugar for 2 minutes. Drizzle butter mixture over pecans. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes. Let cool. Break in pieces and start eating.

title: orange baked chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Coat chicken with onion mixture. Place chicken in shallow casserole dish.
Pour orange juice around chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally until done.
Add carrots the last 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix the eggs and bananas in a bowl.
Sift together the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add to the first mixture.
Lastly, add the butter to the batter.
Stir well.
Put in a well-buttered loaf pan, 9 x 5-inch.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cook chicken and pull off bone.
Put chicken in bottom of deep pan or two 2-quart casserole dishes; add soup, spooning over chicken.
Mix stuffing with broth; stir until moistened.
Spread over chicken mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate confetti balls
directions: Mix in bowl graham cracker crumbs and candies.
Scoop the ice cream into 4 balls.
Roll ice cream balls in crumb mixture.
Place in serving dishes.

title: congo bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Grease cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: coco-nut cookies
directions: Cream
together
butter, sugar and coconut extract; add beaten eggs.
Mix
well;	stir
in
bismix
and potato spuds. Cover bowl and chill 1 hour or longer.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Combine chips, pecans and marshmallow cream in large bowl; do not mix.
In deep saucepan, add sugar, butter and milk.
Over medium heat, let come to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 7 1/2 minutes.
Pour over first mixture; add pecans and blend well. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: italian chili
directions: Fully cook sausage, breaking up with spoonfuls, skin off. Drain off fat.
In another pan with enough olive oil, saute peppers, onion, celery and garlic until soft, not brown.
Add sausage, beans with liquid, tomatoes and seasonings.
Heat on "high" to a boil.
Lower and simmer 45 minutes (good when you can make ahead, refrigerate and skim fat off the top.
Heat slowly, don't let stick to pan).
Cook small macaroni like chili mac or ditalini or elbow.
Add however much you like hot to hot chili. Pass grated Italian cheese; we use Pecorino Romano.
Feeds a crowd!

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and brown sugar in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch skillet.
Beat sugar and egg yolks until light.
Blend alternately with the pineapple juice and flour.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Place pineapple (and cherries and pecans, if desired) in the melted butter and sugar in skillet.
Pour batter over this.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for a few minutes, then invert skillet onto cake plate.

title: london broil with onions
directions: Place steak in shallow glass dish.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over steak.
Cover dish with plastic wrap and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight turning occasionally.
Remove steak and grill 2 inches from medium coals until medium rare.
Meanwhile, put onions in marinade in saucepan and bring to boil, then simmer until onions are tender.
Cut meat across the grain into thin slices. Top with onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt and sour cream in a buttered heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage or candy thermometer registers 234°.
Remove from heat; stir in 2 tablespoons butter.
Beat at high speed with an electric mixer until mixture thickens and begins to lose its gloss (4 to 5 minutes).
Stir in pecans, if desired.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square baking pan or dish; chill until firm.
Store in an airtight container at room temperature.

title: irish trifle
directions: Break cake into pieces and place in trifle or decorative bowl. Sprinkle with sherry and let stand a few minutes.
Make gelatin and when it begins to set, pour over cake.
Make vanilla pudding according to directions and pour over gelatin.
Slice strawberries (or other fruit) and arrange over pudding.
Allow to chill until set.
When ready to serve, cover top with whipped cream and decorate around edges and center with fruit.

title: beef barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients over low heat.
Pour over meat to marinate overnight.

title: homemade wheat bread
directions: In small saucepan, heat milk, brown sugar, salt and oil or margarine, just until warm (125° to 130°) stirring constantly.
Put 2 cups all-purpose flour in large mixing bowl.
Dump yeast on top, let sit.
Add to flour mixture warm liquid and egg.
Beat with electric mixer and dough hooks on low speed 30 seconds or until well mixed.
Add 2 cups wheat flour and as much remaining all-purpose flour as needed for correct consistency.
Set electric mixer on knead and mix for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together in mixing bowl with hands.
Make into balls.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and soda.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300°. Remove from pan at once.

title: grandma edwards' devil's food cake(fit for angels)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add cooled, melted chocolate.
Stir in flour and milk alternately.
Bake in 2 layers at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes, or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool.
Use the following filling and icing.

title: oxtail soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepot on medium-high heat.
Brown oxtails on all sides, removing from pan as they brown.
Add onion and garlic to saucepot.
Cook and stir until tender.
Return oxtails to pot.
Add water, tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 3 hours or until meat is very tender.
Remove oxtails from pot; cool slightly.
Remove meat from bones.
Shred meat.
Return to pot; discard bones.
Add mixed vegetables and cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in pasta.
Makes 6 servings.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Roll into small balls.
Mash with a fork.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain fruit; save the juice.
Mix Jell-O with the 3 cups of hot water.
Add 1 cup of fruit juice.
Add fruit and marshmallows; let sit until thick.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Melt shortening in pan and fry chicken until tender; drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add soup, onion and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix by package directions and bake in 11 1/2 x 15 pan. Cool completely.

title: wassail
directions: Pour all liquid ingredients into coffee maker.
Add spices to basket of coffee maker.
Run through cycle.
You need to use a percolator type, not an automatic drip type coffee maker.

title: peanut or pecan brittle
directions: You will also need a candy thermometer.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter balls(also called buckeyes)
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and melted butter, mixing well. Chill.
Roll into small round balls (about 1 1/2 inches round). Melt paraffin in saucepan over low to medium/low heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted and smooth.
Pick up each ball with a toothpick and dip into the melted chocolate.
(You do not have to cover the ball entirely with chocolate.
You can leave a little place around the toothpick that is not dipped in chocolate, so it will look like a buckeye.)
Place dipped balls on waxed paper.
Store in airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: mango bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into large bowl.
Make a well in center and add all remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into a loaf pan.
Bake at 325°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Slightly beat the eggs.
Mix other ingredients.
Bake at 325° to 350° until done.

title: tailgate beans
directions: In skillet, cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine beef and bacon with remaining ingredients. Pour into a large casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix room temperature cheeses and pecans together until well blended (you may use a blender, mixer or food processor).
Add garlic and onion, then shape into a ball or log.
Roll in parsley flakes and wrap in plastic wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: caramel icing
directions: Whip together and set aside first 3 ingredients.
Put into a saucepan light brown sugar, milk and 1 tablespoon Crisco.
Cook until everything blends and is a light caramel color.
Mix cooked ingredients with first 3 ingredients and mix together.
Ready to spread on cake.

title: apple pie
directions: Thinly slice apples.
Melt oleo and pour over apples.
Combine dry ingredients and mix with apples.
Place in unbaked shell and top with upper crust.
Spread a small amount of milk on top crust and sprinkle with sugar.
Cut some place for air to escape and bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: homemade penrose
directions: Bring all
ingredients, except wieners, to a boil.
Add wieners and simmer 30
minutes.
Put in jars; let stand 2 to 3 days in refrigerator.

title: mexican sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage (crumble).
After sausage is cooked, then drain grease.
Melt cream cheese.
Add salsa and sausage.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine last 2 ingredients.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift together remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar and beat until light (about 2 minutes). Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to egg mixture and blend until smooth (about 2 minutes longer).
Add remaining ingredients and mix very well.
Spoon into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Remove from pan immediately and serve warm or cold.

title: molded grapefruit salad
directions: Combine lemon juice and pineapple juice with water to make 2 cups.
Heat jello until dissolved in hot juice.
Chill.
When it begins to thicken, add pineapple, grapefruit pieces, celery and almonds.

title: old fashioned buttermilk pie
directions: Line 9 or 10-inch pie pan with crust.
Heat oven to 425°. Blend first 6 ingredients together with beater.
Add 2 well beaten eggs.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 30 minutes or until pie is golden brown or inserted knife comes out clean.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and can of pineapple (drained).
Stir in bread cubes until moistened.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: chinese beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, stirring well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Add beets and cook until thickens.

title: orange and tomato toss salad
directions: Core tomatoes; cut into wedges.
In a salad bowl, place tomatoes, lettuce, orange and onion.*
In a glass measure, combine orange juice, vinegar, oil, honey, salt and pepper to taste.
Just before serving, pour over salad; toss gently.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Using two cups water, remove chicken from broth.
Turn crock-pot to high and when broth is boiling, add noodles.
Stir well and cover.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with chicken.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a well floured surface and knead 15 to 20 times.
Pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: 1/2 dozen.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Careful not to overcook.

title: coconut pie(no crust)
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: easiest lasagna ever
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to beef and mix thoroughly.
Spread a thin layer of sauce mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with half of raw lasagna noodles arranged to fit pan.
Top noodles with half of remaining sauce mixture, followed by half of cheese, then remaining noodles.

title: chow mein bars
directions: Melt butterscotch chips.
Add 1 cup peanut butter.
Stir in 1 bag chow mein noodles and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Remove flowerets from broccoli.
Cut stalks into 1-inch pieces.
In saucepan, heat water to boiling.
Add broccoli, celery and onion.
Cook about 10 minutes, or until broccoli is tender. Do not drain.
Place in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Heat margarine until melted, add flour, stirring constantly until smooth.
Stir in chicken broth.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in broccoli, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Heat just to boiling.
Stir in whipping cream.
Heat just until hot, do not boil.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix butter, flour and pecans together and press in square cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip and spread on crust.
Mix lemon pudding and milk together.
Spread on top of cheese mixture; top with additional Cool Whip.
This dessert is pretty with nuts and slices of lemon on top.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil in a large Dutch oven.
Stir in macaroni.
Return to a rapid bowl and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.

title: shake and bake mix
directions: Mix all together.
Shake fish or chicken with this.
Store in airtight container.

title: toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix first 4 ingredients with fork in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stir in Bisquick until moistened. Press mixture evenly into pan.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes or until light brown.
Immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips and let stand until softened, 3 to 4 minutes; spread evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Makes approximately 32 bars.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Fold carrots, cheese and celery soup together.
Put into greased casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs, 1/4 cup milk, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, allspice or nutmeg.
Add meat.
Mix well.
Shape into 30 meatballs.
In a large skillet, cook meatballs in margarine or butter, half at a time, over medium heat about 10 minutes or until no pink remains, turning to brown evenly.
Remove from skillet, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings. Drain meatballs on paper towels.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle half the mixture on one side of the round steak and pound on.
Repeat for other side. Cut meat into pieces.

title: vanderwahl cake(two 9-inch layers)
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure.
Add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Cream butter with 1 1/2 cups of sugar until the mixture is light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Add vanilla and blend.
Beat egg whites until frothy throughout, then gradually beat in reserved half cup of sugar and continue to beat until the mixture holds in soft peaks.
Fold lightly but thoroughly through the batter.
Pour into two deep greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans and bake in a 375° oven for about 30 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove from the oven and allow to stand in pans 5 minutes.
Then turn out on wire racks to cool and frost as desired.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt oleo over medium heat.
Stir in flour.
Blend well. Gradually stir half and half and bouillon cubes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened slightly.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and heat until just melted.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine
all ingredients and bake in tube pan, that has been greased
and
floured,
for one hour at 325°.
(Test for doneness.)

title: sweet and tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine onion, garlic and oil in 1-quart casserole; cover with lid.
Microwave on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients; cover.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes.
Sauce can be covered and refrigerated for up to 2 weeks. Makes 1
1/2 cups.

title: sandy's cutout cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Blend in flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Cover and chill dough 2 to 3 hours.
Divide dough in half.
Keep rest in refrigerator.
Roll out on lightly floured cloth or table.
Cut into desired shapes or use cookie cutters.
Transfer cookies to a lightly greased baking sheet.
Repeat with second half of dough. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Split English muffins in half.
Combine crab meat, cheese, butter, mayo, seasoned salt and garlic powder in bowl; mix with hands (easier).
Spread mixture on muffins.
Put muffin halves back in original package with wax paper between layers.
Freeze for at least 3 hours.
Cut each muffin in 1/4-inch pieces and place on cookie sheet.
Bake or broil until light brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in casserole dish.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Place chicken in a lightly oiled Pyrex or Corning Ware pan. Mix chestnuts, mushrooms, celery, soup and mayonnaise together. Pour mixture over chicken.
Mix stuffing with melted butter. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is cooked completely.

title: checkerboard cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 3 ingredients.
Blend the flour and salt into mix.
Divide dough in half.
Tint half the dough with any food coloring.
Chill, if desired.
Take 1 teaspoon of each color and roll into pencil-like roll.
Alternate colors.
Use beaten egg white in between to stack layers about 3 wide and 3 high.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Slice 1/4 inch thick and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: beef (rollanden) rolls
directions: Butcher will cut thin steaks (about 1/4-inch) on request.
Cut steaks into 3 x 6-inch pieces; pound to tenderize.
Salt and pepper each strip and place 1/2 strip of bacon on each.
Roll up strips and secure with thread or toothpick.
Brown on all sides; remove from pan.
Make gravy from stock with flour and cold water; shake well to remove lumps.
Slowly add mixture to frypan, stirring constantly.
Continue to add water to consistency desired.
Add new potatoes, onions and baby carrots; return beef rolls to pan.
Cook on medium heat, covered, until vegetables are tender.

title: blueberry-banana pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Slice bananas on pie shell.
Pour cheese mixture over bananas.
Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: pineapple pudding cream cheesecake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cool.

title: angel pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg whites until very stiff; add cream of tartar and slowly add 1 cup sugar.
Spread meringue into a well buttered glass pie plate.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust of graham crumbs and 1 stick butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar and eggs.
Beat with 1 stick butter.
Pour over crust for first layer.
Drain pineapple. Reserve the juice. Slice the bananas and dip in pineapple juice. Layer the bananas and pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over the top. Top with cherries and nuts. Chill at least 8 hours.

title: nutty waffle cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat margarine and brown sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg and milk.
Beat well.
Mix flour and baking powder; add to mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on waffle iron. Cook same as waffles.
Cool on rack.
Frost, if desired.
Makes 20 to 24.

title: nort branch cauliflower
directions: Cook vegetable in boiling salted water until tender.
Mix can of soup with sour cream and mayonnaise.
Season mix with salt and pepper.
Place cooked cauliflower in casserole dish that has been treated with margarine or cooking spray.
Pour soup mixture over vegetable.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Garnish with leftover cookies.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain well. Put in Dutch oven. Add mushrooms, tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce and green beans. Add salt and pepper. Bring to boil. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: old fashion oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients (sugar, flour, baking powder) and milk together.
Pour this over melted butter.
Do not mix!
Add peaches.
Mix cinnamon and sugar. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: racille's chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix onion, beans, sauce, water and seasonings.
Add meat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: hamburg chop suey
directions: Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Bake 15 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with chow mein noodles.
One half recipe can be used for small family.

title: crunchy ice cream dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Toast on cookie sheet for 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish to layer 1/2 mixture on bottom, softened ice cream in second layer, other 1/2 mixture on top.
Return to freezer.
This serves several people.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend ingredients.
Form into walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown. May be frozen and reheated. Bake on broiler pan, sprayed with Pam.
Do not let balls touch each other. Do not add water or other moisture to this recipe.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place ingredients in pan in order given.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: hidden valley oyster crackers
directions: Put crackers in gallon size Ziploc bag. Pour oil in bag and seal. Toss to coat. Add seasoning package. Seal and toss again. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix well with dressing.
Save 1/4 of the dressing and set aside.
Mix all ingredients with the squash. Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining dressing. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and press firmly on the bottom of a 9-inch spring form pan.

title: john-y-brown pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and 2 cups sugar and let set for 2 hours so sugar can dissolve.
Make jello as on the box.
After it is cool, add all the rest and stir well.
Don't drain the pineapple too well.
Put in the refrigerator.

title: hot poppy seed ham rolls
directions: Mix together the butter, poppy seed, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Slice each roll almost through, leaving it hinged on one side.
Spread each side of roll with the butter mixture.
Place many layers of ham and a slice of cheese on each roll; replace top of roll.

title: diane's sausage casserole
directions: Layer stuffing, sausage and mushrooms (in order given) in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, milk, eggs and mustard.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°. Remove from oven and put grated cheese on top.
Return to oven and cook 10 minutes more.
May make this the night before and refrigerate.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: Cook off the chicken and save 2 cups of broth.
Break or cut chicken into pieces.
Fry onion and green pepper in salad oil. Stir in broth and add all other ingredients except flour and chicken.
Thicken with flour to desired thickness.
Add chicken and simmer for 1/2 hour before serving on buns.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa and milk to hard boil; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Combine butter, peanut butter, vanilla and oats into first mixture.
Beat until mixture thickens.
Spoon onto wax paper.
That's all, no baking.

title: shoestring salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes. Toss all together and add potatoes just before serving.

title: chocolate pecan fudge
directions: Melt in microwave for 2 minutes at 50% power.
Stir. Cook 2 more minutes.
Stir in 3 cups chopped pecans.
Put in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Refrigerate to set.

title: pork roast with raisins
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Trim fat from pork roast.
Place pork on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Mix remaining ingredients, except Raisin Sauce; sprinkle over pork.
Insert meat thermometer so tip is in center of thickest part of roast and does not rest on fat.

title: tomato garlic bread
directions: In blender, whiz 1 cup of the tomato juice and the dates until smooth.
Put into large mixing bowl and add remaining juice. Sprinkle the yeast into bowl and stir until yeast dissolves.
Stir in garlic salt and Italian seasoning.
Add the whole heat flour and enough plain unbleached flour to make a fairly stiff dough. Knead well.
Put in Pam sprayed bowl.
Cover with a damp cloth and let rise until double.
Punch down; shape into loaves.
Put into 2 large loaf pans (that have been lightly sprayed with Pam) and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour.

title: quick and easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil.
Remove from heat and add chocolate bits.
Stir until melted.

title: sauerbraten
directions: In 2 or 3-quart saucepan, combine all listed ingredients up to and including the bay leaves. Bring to a boil; let cool to room temperature. Pour over beef roast in a deep crock, or stainless steel or enamel pot. The marinade should come half way up over the roast. Add water if necessary. Turn meat to cover. Cover the pan and refrigerate 2-3 days, turning the roast twice per day. Remove the roast from marinade and pat dry. Strain the marinade and reserve the liquid.

title: fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, combine all ingredients.
Heat and stir until well blended.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan and cool.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Grease 9 inch ovenproof skillet, place in oven to heat. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, then pour into heated skillet. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.

title: cranberry and orange bread
directions: Add pecans and cranberry sauce to muffin mix.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bread tests done.
Invert onto wire rack.
Slice and serve warm. Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chicken.
Put in on top. Cook at 350° for 1 hour covered with foil for the last 15 minutes. Take cover off.
Let chicken brown.
Real good.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken

title: apple tapioca
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nutmeg, in a saucepan.
Mix lightly and let stand 5 minutes.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer until apples are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan with milk.
Place shredded potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pour butter and milk mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Thoroughly mix cheese, egg, milk and salt.
Cut slices of bread in half.
Toast on 1 side.
Spread untoasted side with the cheese mixture and place under broiler until brown (cheese is puffy and toasted).

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Pour enough water over horseradish mixture to make a paste.

title: yuletide cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar, egg, vanilla and salt.
Add flour and mix well.
Add oatmeal and blend.
Add pecans and blend. If too dry, add a tablespoon of water.
Form into balls the size of a small walnut.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Put into small balls, size of a walnut.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Do not flatten.
Bake 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: crispy chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, soup, mayonnaise, celery, rice, lemon juice and onion.
Place in a greased casserole; sprinkle with corn flakes and top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple-cranberry crunch
directions: Mix apples, cranberries and granulated sugar; place in bottom of ungreased shallow pan.

title: hot baked chicken salad
directions: May add 1/2 cup toasted almonds, pecans or water chestnuts.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until creamy, then add eggs, beating 10 full minutes or until it is no longer gritty.
Pour into baked pie shell or use graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Freezes great.

title: grandma's gingerbread cookies
directions: Beat butter with sugar and molasses.
Mix in egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to wet mixture.
Mix well.
Chill in freezer 1 hour or refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream the shortening until like thick cream.
Add sugar a little at a time until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten egg yolks and blend thoroughly.
Add enough hot water to the cocoa to make a smooth paste, then add enough more to make 1 cupful of cocoa mixture.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add alternately with the sour milk to which the vanilla has been added.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in carefully the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into 2 greased and lightly floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Frost with desired frosting.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix together the margarine and white sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In large mixer bowl with mixer at medium speed, cream butter, salad oil, confectioners sugar and 1 cup granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and continue beating, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Gradually add dry ingredients and continue mixing until just combined.
Wrap and refrigerate dough at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets; set aside.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in additional granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheets.
Press each ball with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove immediately to wire racks to cool.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown steak in oil.
Add 1/4 cup water and simmer 15 minutes. Add tomato soup, Worcestershire, onion, brown sugar, chili powder, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 hour on low.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package until almost tender.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Divide between 2 well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dishes.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix salt, corn, cornmeal, baking powder, bell pepper, cooking oil, eggs, jalapeno pepper, green onion, and sour cream.
Pour half of the batter in the pan and sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Pour the rest of the batter into the pan and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Combine the sugar and eggs and mix well.
Sift the dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: One box of graham crackers contains three individually wrapped packages of crackers; use one package for each layer of this indulgent dessert.
Line bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 inch baking dish with one-third of honey graham crackers.
Whisk together pudding mix and milk; add whipped topping, stirring until mixture thickens.
Spread half of pudding mixture over graham crackers.
Repeat layers with one-third graham crackers and remaining pudding mixture.
Top with remaining graham crackers. Spread with chocolate frosting.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.

title: old south cucumber lime pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamel ware for 12 hours or overnight.
Do not use aluminum. Remove sliced cucumbers from lime water.
Discard lime water. Rinse 3 times in fresh cold water.
Soak 3 hours in ice water. Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and mixed pickling spices in a large pot.
Bring to a low boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Remove syrup from heat and add sliced cucumbers.
Soak 5 - 6 hours or overnight.
Boil slices in the syrup 35 minutes.
Fill sterilized jars with hot slices.
Pour hot syrup over the slices, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Cap each jar when filled.
Process pints 10 minutes in a boiling water bath canner.
Test jars for airtight seals according to manufacturers instructions.

title: tarzan's cooler
directions: Combine juice and banana in blender.
Cover and process until smooth.
Makes 2 cups; 99 calories per cup.

title: fresh tomato sauce(a relish)
directions: Chop peppers and onions in coarse grinder or blender.
Put in colander, squeeze down to remove all juices.
Put tomatoes in hot water and peel.
Put tomatoes in colander and squeeze to remove all juices (throw all juices out).
Put all the pulp in a large pot (not aluminum).
Add sugar, vinegar and salt; simmer for 2 hours. (You can add Tabasco sauce if you like.)
Seal in tight 1/2-pint jars.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soup, tomatoes, mushrooms, cheese and sauces.
Cook until cheese melts.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, starting with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: honey-spice ring
directions: Combine
raisins,
apples
and
boiling water in a bowl. Let stand
for
10 minutes, then mix in honey, salt, cinnamon, allspice,
nutmeg,
cloves
and
oil;
set aside.
Mix together flour, wheat germ, baking soda and walnuts.
Combine with apple mixture.
Pour into well greased angel cake pan ring.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve plain or topped with 10x powdered sugar.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Finish filling freezer with sweet milk after all ingredients are mixed and put in freezer.
Other fruit may be used.

title: oriental burritos
directions: For filling, cook turkey, onion and garlic in skillet til turkey is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Drain off fat. Place meat in a large bowl.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in same skillet, stir-fry broccoli slaw for 2 minutes.
Stir broccoli slaw, the stir-fry sauce, five-spice powder, garlic pepper and celery salt into meat.
Stir in shredded cheese.
Heat tortillas to soften.
Spoon about 3/4 cup filling onto each tortilla just below center.
Fold bottom edge of tortilla up and over filling.
Fold in opposite sides just til they meet.
Roll up.
Secure with toothpicks.
Heat 2 tablespoons of remaining oil in wok or skillet. Cook burritos, 3 or 4 at a time over medium heat about 4 minutes or until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in oven.
(Burritos may be baked to warm instead of fried.)

title: easy double fudge cake mix cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet with Crisco shortening.
Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Drop in balls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mom's five-flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar. Add eggs; combine flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk. Stir in flavorings.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set flour mixture aside.
Melt butter.
Add to brown sugar and stir together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts. Add mixture to flour mixture.
Mix all together.
Grease pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine sugar, egg yolks and oil all together; beat 3 minutes. Beat egg whites to a stiff peak.
Add to flour and sugar; beat for 3 minutes.
Add pecans and bake in 3 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk for two minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 mix over graham crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Pour remaining mix over second layer of crackers.
Add third layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Mix remaining 6 ingredients until smooth.
Spread over graham crackers. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: oven barbecued chicken(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except chicken in a saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Wash and dry chicken and place in a large baking pan.
Pour half of barbecue sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes, basting with remaining sauce every 15 minutes.
Or, chicken may be immersed in sauce, then removed and cooked over charcoal, basting frequently.
Serves 4, 260 calories per serving.
Serve with boiled potatoes and put the barbecue sauce on potatoes.

title: mud-pie cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Make 3 holes in the mixture.
Put the oil in the first hole, the vinegar in second hole and vanilla in the third hole.
Pour water over all. Stir until it is mixed and smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: merry cherry parfait
directions: Prepare brownies as directed; cool and cut in small cubes. Make pudding as directed on package.
Retaining 1 1/2 cups topping, fold remainder into pudding.

title: diabetic waldorf salad
directions: Toss together apples and lemon juice in medium-size bowl. Stir in raisins, grapes and celery.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix everything together except the crumbs.
Pour into a shallow casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs around the edge.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Chop avocados, then mash with fork or mixer, mixing in with lemon juice. Add salt, onion, softened cream cheese and milk. Make ahead of time to allow flavors to blend.

title: red french dressing
directions: Blend 2 minutes on low in blender.

title: fruit cake
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir until well blended; pour into 8-inch tube pan (not Bundt), coated with 4 tablespoons shortening and 2 tablespoons flour.
Bake at 325° until tester comes out clean (approximately 2 hours).
Cool on rack for at least 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix drained beans and cream of mushroom soup.
Put in casserole dish; layer with fried onion rings.
Bake in moderate oven until heated through.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix above ingredients in pan; bring to slow boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Skim foam from top.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken breasts over rice.
Mix water with cream of mushroom soup and pour over chicken and rice.
Sprinkle Lipton onion soup over top.
Cover with tinfoil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake additional 1/2 hour.
Serve hot.

title: delicious chicken "italian"
directions: Combine lemon juice, oil, parsley, salt and pepper in a bowl. Place chicken halves in large shallow baking dish.
Pour marinade over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
May be grilled or baked in a shallow roasting pan for 1 hour at 350°, brushing often with marinade.

title: salt substitute
directions: The recipe makes a flavorful seasoning to use in place of salt in cooking and at the table.
Start by adding a small amount to your food, then gradually increase according to your preference.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in pan on both sides, then place in baking dish.
Mix ingredients in bowl, then pour over chops.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese quiche
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package, except using 2 tablespoons milk. Add 2 eggs.
Mix well. Spread over bottom and sides of greased 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish. Toss cheese with flour. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cover loosely with foil. Continue baking 20 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Stir all ingredients together; add Bisquick last.
Drop by spoonfuls onto heated, greased skillet.
Fry like pancakes. Makes 10 to 12 patties.

title: creole rice
directions: Place red pepper, onion, celery, garlic and vegetable oil in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan and stir to combine.
Cook, uncovered, on High in microwave for 4 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir in rice, tomatoes and juice, hot pepper sauce and water.
Cook, uncovered, for 25 minutes, stirring 3 times, on High in microwave. Remove from oven.
Stir in lemon juice and black pepper to taste. Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: chicken divan
directions: Brown bread crumbs in 1 teaspoon melted butter.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Bone chicken and cut in chunks.
Boil for 45 minutes. Combine in bowl the soup, mayonnaise, milk, curry and lemon and pour over meat and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a casserole dish.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, oleo and milk, stirring constantly, to soft-ball stage.
Add chips, Marshmallow Fluff and peanut butter.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs in butter.
Next, layer coconut, chips and chopped nuts over the crumbs.
Gently press down.
Swirl the Eagle Brand milk evenly over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken, rice and vegetables
directions: Mix the rice, onion, green pepper, celery and salt in a small bowl.
Add the water; stir to blend.
Divide the whole chicken breasts; you will need four pieces.
Tear 4 pieces of foil about 15 inches long.
Divide the rice mixture into four portions, one portion to each foil piece.
Place the foil onto a cookie sheet with edges of foil turned up so liquid does not run out.
Place 1 chicken piece on top of each portion of rice mixture.
Blend the soup and milk; spoon equally over the chicken.
Thaw the mixed vegetables just enough to separate.
Arrange the vegetables around the chicken.
Bring long ends of foil up and fold carefully.
Fold the two sides up and seal so juice will not run out.
Place packs on a cookie sheet in a preheated 375° oven.
Bake for 1 hour. Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 53 g, protein 22 g, fat 11 g, calories 399.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with walnuts or pecans.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Boil and drain spinach in salt water.
While hot, add cream cheese (cut in small pieces) and butter.
Mix until completely melted.
Quarter artichoke hearts and slice water chestnuts very thin.
Mix with spinach.
Pour in baking dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix all together; add enough mayonnaise to moisten (about 1 cup).
Bake 20 minutes at 325° or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with rye crackers.
Enjoy!

title: peach delight(and it is delightful)
directions: Drain peaches and mash with a potato masher.
Add 1 cup of sugar and all the remaining syrup drained from the peaches. Bring sugar-syrup to a
boil, then cook gently, stirring for 5 minutes. Remove from
stove.
Add
jello;
stir
until
jello dissolves. Fill 2 pint
jars.
Let cool, then keep in refrigerator.
(Really good on toast for breakfast.)

title: coconut chiffon cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan well, then sprinkle sides and bottom with mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Set pan aside.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Fold in 1 can coconut pecan frosting mix.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 300°.
The mixture of sugars help to glaze the cake. (Very moist cake.)

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in square baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Cut butter over cake mix; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: microwave two minute velvet fudge
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Microwave chocolate chips and the condensed milk uncovered in a 2-quart bowl on High 2 minutes. Stir until smooth.
Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla, then the walnuts until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan and spread evenly.
Chill until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cut into 16 (2-inch) squares.
Store tightly covered in a cool place for up to 2 weeks.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix well.
Add sour milk.
Melt chocolate and butter over hot water; mix well and add.
Sift flour before measuring.
Combine dry ingredients (flour, soda, baking powder and salt); add to batter and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add gradually the boiling water.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Let cool before icing.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Heat milk over medium heat until bubbles form around pan. Then watch for milk to rise.
When milk rises about 1/8 of an inch and foam appears on top, take milk off heat.
Let cool.
Beat eggs, vanilla and salt, then sugar.
Blend into milk.
Then add Grape-Nuts and raisins.
Pour into glass pan and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Sit glass pan inside pan with water 1/3 full.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in cup.
Add vinegar and stir. Pour into jars after pickling cucumbers are packed in tightly. Fill jar with vinegar.
Add 1/2 teaspoon rock alum to each jar. Cover tightly and shake often for a few hours.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Place sausage in crock-pot.
Add water, halfway up on sausage. Add jelly and mustard.
Simmer on low.
This is very good served with Fried Okra Salad (in cookbook) and baked beans.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Wash eggplants and cut in half.
Scoop out pulp to about 1/2-inch of skin.
Brown onion in oil.
Dice pulp.
Add pulp, tomatoes and bread crumbs together with browned onion.
Fill eggplant shells with mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°. Serves 4.

title: chicken salad finger sandwiches
directions: Bake chicken breasts in foil until well-done.
Remove all bones, skin and gristle.
Let chicken cool completely.
Chop chicken in fine pieces.
Mix first 6 ingredients and let refrigerate about 2 to 3 hours.
Trim bread crusts and cut sandwiches into 3 pieces lengthwise.

title: pink rhubarb refresher(usa)
directions: Cook rhubarb in boiling water to a mush (cut rhubarb but do not peel).
Press through a sieve.
Measure the juice.
For each cup juice add 1/3 cup sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill.
For each cup rhubarb juice add 1/2 cup grapefruit juice.
Add the 1/4 cup lemon juice to the entire mixture.
Just before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale.
Serves 24.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth.
Mix rice and other ingredients. Place in 2-quart casserole.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling together, adding pecans last. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 400° (hot) oven for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Form into a ball or roll. Refrigerate for a few hours.
Serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy blueberry coffeecake
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cover with blueberries.
Combine pecans and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread over blueberries.
Melt butter, add oil.
Add 1 cup sugar, flour and eggs.
Blend then spread over blueberries.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Wash shrimp and remove muscle.
Drain.
Place in blender. Place in cheese in blender along with other ingredients.
Blend well and serve.

title: crunchy brunchy
directions: Preheat oven to 440°.
Grease small cookie sheet.
Melt together in a large pan over low heat the butter, brown sugar and honey.
Stir until sugar is melted.
Remove from heat; mix in the oatmeal, raisins and nuts.
Spread mixture on greased cookie sheet; bake until well browned.
Take pan out; set aside to cool. (I mix occasionally while browning.)
Crumble into small pieces with your hands.
Store in tightly closed can or plastic bag. Serve in a bowl with lots of cold milk, or eat as a snack.

title: millionaire pies (2)
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in pie shell at 350° until firm. Serve with whipped cream.

title: pork chop roast
directions: Combine mustard and brown sugar; spread on pork chops.
Place a chop vertically at one end of oblong baking pan, fat edge up. Next to it, place a pineapple ring, a green pepper ring and an onion slice.
Repeat until all are used.
Fasten together with skewers.
Pour pineapple juice over all.
Cover pan with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Cook rice as directed.
Brown celery and onions in margarine.
Mix all together with some cheese whiz.
Pour in baking dish & top with more cheese whiz.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together in a large bowl all dry ingredients.
In a blender, add eggs, oil and enough zucchini to fill to top of blender. Blend until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake 50-60 mins.

title: laurie barnson's mint brownies
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar until light.
Combine all other ingredients.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 40 minutes.
Don't overcook!
Let cool; frost with Mint Frosting.

title: ham balls
directions: Beat together eggs and prepared mustard.
Mix cornflakes, ham loaf and milk together with first mixture.
Shape into balls.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: In a large glass bowl, combine pineapple, oranges, banana, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and almonds.
Fold in yogurt. Chill well before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Roll coconut bar cookies into crumbs.
Mix with 1 cube melted butter and press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix eggs, 2 cubes butter and 1 box powdered sugar.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Pour over cookie mixture.
Slice bananas and place over the topping, then cover the bananas with the crushed pineapple.
Then cover with Cool Whip and top with nuts and cherries.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spray dish with nonstick cooking spray. Pour ingredients in 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top and brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Make sure cheese is room temperature.
Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate so you can shape into balls.
Use margarine or cooking oil on hands to prevent the mixture from sticking to hands.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in waxed paper. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Defrost strawberries.
Beat eggs in a bowl until fluffy; add oil, sugar and defrosted strawberries.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add flour mixture to strawberry mixture and mix well.
Stir in nuts that have been mixed with 1 tablespoon flour. Pour in a greased and floured bread pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: pineapple salad
directions: In a large bowl, gradually stir the undrained pineapple into the cream cheese. Stir in the pudding mix. Fold in the pineapple and whipped topping. Cover and chill until serving time.

title: lasagna
directions: Lightly brown beef and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes (put through blender or cut with edge of spoon), paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic, pepper and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: While grits are hot, add butter and bacon-cheese spread.
Let cool and add milk and eggs.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Add 1 cup grated cheese to top and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.
Dip with your favorite snack crackers.

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend cream cheese, chili sauce, parsley, onion and pepper sauce until smooth.
Add tuna gradually until all is thoroughly blended.
Pack in a 4-cup bowl as a mold.
Chill at least 3 hours. Unmold on lettuce and serve with crisp sesame crackers.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: harry vermont schoppert's fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa until completely blended in saucepan.
Add milk to the mixture and stir until all sugar and cocoa are dissolved.
Put mixture on stove at low heat until it comes to a boil.
Stir once in a while so mixture will not stick to bottom of pan.

title: mimi's hot rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, sugar, salt and Crisco in large bowl; let cool.
In a small bowl, mix yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and warm water. Add beaten egg to first mixture.
Add yeast mixture and then flour. Cover and let rise.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Make into rolls or will make 2 loaves.

title: savory rice
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water; set aside.
In large skillet over low heat, melt butter.
Add onion; cook 5 minutes.
Add rice; stir until coated with butter.
Add bouillon liquid and seasonings. Mix well.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: play dough
directions: Add ingredients in order.
Mix with hands when cool enough. Add flour slowly until easily handled.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put all ingredients, except pecans and pie shell, in blender or processor.
Mix until thoroughly well blended.
With spoon, combine mixture and pecans.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for the first 5 minutes, then at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes. Pie is done when springy to touch.
It firms up as it cools.

title: aunt joyce's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; boil gently for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Mix quickly.
Turn into 2 (7 x 8-inch pans) or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Butter pans real good.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add other ingredients and blend well. Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs until light; add milk and butter and add to flour mixture all at once.
Stir only enough to dampen flour.
Drop by spoonfuls into buttered muffin pans and bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
If you wish berry muffins, reserve 1/4 cup of the flour; use to dredge 1 cup blueberries and add to mixture.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of food coloring and cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Add salt to buttermilk.
Add alternately to creamed mixture; blend well.
Add vanilla.
Mix soda and vinegar together.
Add into batter.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Place all ingredients in pan with beef. Cover with a little water.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: cheesy cauliflower(microwave)
directions: Clean head of cauliflower.
Leave head intact.
Put in bowl with water.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Open one side.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Spread sauce over cauliflower.
Top with cheese.
Microwave, uncovered, 1 minute to heat topping and melt cheese.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar in the water.
Add lemon juice, bananas and pineapple juice.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer to allow time to thaw to a slush prior to use.
Add 7-Up to a recipe when served.

title: muddy buddies(snacks)
directions: Mix chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter in a microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave for 1 minute.
Stir and microwave for another 30 seconds.
Mix in Chex cereal, one cup at a time. Make sure all pieces are covered evenly.
Put about 1 cup of powdered sugar into a plastic bag.
Mix in cereal a little at a time.
Shake until it is well coated.
Then serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serves 8 people.

title: apricot nut snack loaf(recipe from england)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add nuts, apricots and cherries.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Stir only until flour is dampened. Turn into a well-greased 9 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Push batter up into corners of pan, leaving the center slightly hollowed.
For a well-rounded loaf, allow batter to stand in pan 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal-raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pan or use cupcake liners. In a large bowl with fork, cream shortening and sugar until blended.
Add egg whites and beat until fairly smooth.
Add oats, flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, baking powder, applesauce and 2 tablespoons of water.
Stir until moistened.
Fold raisins into batter.
Spoon batter into muffin pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden and toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla, cook for 7 minutes in double boiler, beating constantly at high speed.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Frost cake.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Bake in oven at 300° or 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cook in oblong pan and stir once or twice.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients; let set, then mix the next 4 ingredients.
Cook and cool.
When cool, add the whipped cream with sugar and flavor.
Pour over set jello mixture; top with grated County Line cheese.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add drained pineapple and partially thawed strawberries.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Spread sour cream on top and remaining jello mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together;
blend well, but do not overmix.
Shape
6 oval patties 1/2-inch thick.
Broil under a preheated broiler
until done as desired, about 4 to 5 minutes on each side.

title: louisiana joe(main dish)
directions: Prepare cornbread as package directs.
Cut into 6 pieces.
In skillet, brown meat with onion, green pepper and garlic; drain. Stir in tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over cornbread.
Prep and cook time:
30 minutes.

title: beans
directions: Clean beans by picking out small stones from package and rinse.
Pour beans into pot of boiling water.
Add salt and garlic salt to taste.
Cook on medium, lowering heat when boiling.
Keep covered.
Keep water over beans, adding hot water when needed. Choose bean variety of choice.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients with hand mixer.
Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: noodle burger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in a skillet.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Turn into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until noodles are done and liquid slightly thickens.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: candy like cookies(no bake cookie)
directions: In top of
a
double boiler, melt butter and chocolate. Blend with a whisk, then add oats and combine well.
Form into golf size balls.
This mixture is both crumbly and wet and you might
not think it
is
going
to
hold
together,
but
surprise...it does. Place in
a waxed paper lined pan and chill. When the cookies are firm,
roll them in confectioners sugar. Store them in the refrigerator, but allow them to come to room temperature 30 minutes before serving.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients, except milk.
Let stand several hours. Stir often to dissolve sugar.
Add milk and pour into ice cream churn/freezer.
Freeze until firm.

title: queen anne cookies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and spread into a greased pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut into small squares and roll in powdered sugar while they are still warm.
It is very important not to overbake these cookies!!!

title: wendy's sauerbraten beef roll
directions: Spread one side beef with mustard.
Stir together all seasonings with yogurt; spread over steak.
Roll up tightly.
Lay on foil lined mast pan; cover tightly and chill 24 to 48 hours. Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove meat from refrigerator; uncover and pour wine or juice over all.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour. Uncover; baste 2 to 3 times during baking.
Recover each time. Finally, uncover; bake, uncovered, until fork-tender.
(More wine or juice may be added during baking to keep moist.)

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl cream oil and sugar.
Stir in eggs and pumpkin. In separate bowl, blend flour, soda, salt, and pumpkin spice.
Add sugar mixture, stir until blended.
Pour into greased loaf pans.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: In a bowl, combine water, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper. Slice cucumbers and marinate in vinegar mixture 2 to 3 hours. Drain. Gently mix cucumbers with sour cream.

title: sunday steak
directions: Brown steak; drain off grease.
Slice onions over steak.
Add water.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until steak is tender.
If sauce gets too thick, add a little water.

title: company salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add juice, then egg.
Cook slowly until thick.
Cool.
Then add Cool Whip.
Spread on Jell-O.
Grate cheese over top.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter over a double boiler.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper.
Pour mixture onto cookie sheet, then cover with chocolate chips; swirl together.
Cool completely.
Cut and serve.

title: company chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken in pan.
Distribute cheese over top of chicken.
Pour soup over chicken and cheese. Sprinkle stuffing on top of that.
Melt margarine and drizzle over mixture.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: earlene's (ky.) "fried" chicken
directions: First, take 2 cups flour. Add paprika and salt. Set aside. Next put 1 cup of either one of the soups.
Add Good Seasons Italian dressing mix powder in a plastic bag and shake up.
Next add chicken pieces in bag and coat.

title: orange pear salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot pear juice.
Add softened cream cheese and water.
Let cool until slightly thickened.
Add Cool Whip and diced pears.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover the bottom with bread.
Cook ground sausage or bacon and drain, then cover the top of the bread. In a bowl, beat the eggs, milk, Mrs. Dash and mustard.
Pour over the meat and bread cubes.
Put in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mothers rice
directions: Wash rice twice and look through.
Cook until tender with 2 1/2 cups water.
Add sugar.
Beat 3 eggs.
Add milk stirring as you put over heat.
Let boil up good.
Add nutmeg and cool.

title: sausage strata
directions: Saute sausage, onion and fresh herbs.
Mix eggs, milk and mustards.
Place bread cubes on bottom of muffin tin cups.
Next, place sausage on top of bread cubes.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Pour egg mixture over and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 20.

title: nutty pink salad
directions: Stir together first three ingredients, then fold in cool whip and pecans.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
(Will keep for two weeks in freezer.)

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix with apples.
Turn into a pastry lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits in top.
Cover edge with a 1 to 2-inch strip of foil to prevent burning.
Remove the last 15 minutes.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until crust and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.

title: famous mushroom casserole
directions: Place half of bread crumbs in bottom of buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt, pepper, dry mustard and red pepper.
Separately, saute stems and caps of mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Season with Worcestershire, prepared mustard and lemon juice.
Layer stems over cheese.
Add remaining bread cubes, egg mixture, 1/4 pound cheese and 1/4 cup butter. Top with mushroom caps.
Refrigerate 8 hours to 2 days.
Top with mushroom soup.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: Slice strawberries into a bowl and sprinkle with Equal.
Let it sit while you mix the cheesecake according to directions on box.
Fold in strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add butter, water, vanilla extract and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: frozen coleslaw
directions: Combine vegetables; sprinkle with salt and let stand 1 hour. Drain mixture if water accumulates.

title: vanilla wafer crunch
directions: In large mixing bowl, add butter, powdered sugar and beaten eggs.
Blend in Cool Whip, strawberries and pecans.
Press crushed vanilla wafers in bottom of pie dish.
Pour mixture over wafers. Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: plantation pecan pie
directions: Beat egg slightly; add sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla. Beat gently until combined.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° until set, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: popover pizza
directions: Mix, cook and drain.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Put all ingredients, except spices in crock-pot in order listed.
Mix spices together (add additional chili powder and/or cayenne pepper for spicier chili) and sprinkle over contents in crock-pot.
Stir once.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or high for 5 to 6 hours.
For crock-pots with removable pots, this can be assembled the night before and put on first thing in the morning to cook all day!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder, salt and peanuts.
Roll in small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork tines.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: apricot sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients in an electric blender until apricots are fully pureed.
Pour into freezer container of 1 gallon electric freezer.
Freeze according to freezer instructions. Makes 2 quarts.

title: sour cream coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugar together in mixing bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together. Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream and milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix well after each addition.
Spoon half of the batter into prepared pan.

Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Sprinkle mixture evenly over first half of batter. Spoon remaining batter over filling. Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack and cool completely.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: angel gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Make them in muffin tins.
Test it with a toothpick.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos.
Blend butter and cream cheese.
Blend pudding and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer Oreos and pudding mix, beginning and ending with Oreos.

title: mazetti
directions: Cook the hamburger and sausage; drain.
Put this in a bowl with the mushroom soup, tomato soup or sauce, chili powder and onion and green pepper, which have been sauteed in 1/2 stick margarine.
Cook the egg noodles.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Place sliced potatoes on foil.
Sprinkle heavily with garlic salt and not so much regular salt.
Distribute chopped onion over potatoes.
Scoop 3 or 4 tablespoons butter over this.
Seal and bake in oven at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Take out of oven. Unwrap and sprinkle cheese all over potatoes.
Seal until cheese has melted.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg. Alternate flour and salt with milk.
Fold in coconut and extracts. Pour batter into a greased tube pan and put in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over warm cake.

title: tracey's garbage cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients together.
Sift together next 4 ingredients.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed ingredients.
Add rest of optional "garbage" or whatever you desire.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: frankfurter bake
directions: Cook noodles as directed. Drain and return to pan. Stir in cheese, milk, butter and flour. Pour into large baking dish. Cut franks and combine with remaining ingredients. Stir to coat franks. Spoon over noodles. Bake at 375° until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate blanc mange
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add boiling water. Stir until smooth.
Cook slowly until it begins to thicken.
Add milk and slowly bring to a boil; boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and chill.

title: zesty noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix sour cream and cottage cheese together. Put drained noodles in the mixture.
Melt butter and saute onions and meat until browned.
Add tomato sauce to meat and mix well.
