Add remaining ingredients to meat mixture and mix well. Put a layer of noodle mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan, then a layer of meat mixture alternating, ending with the meat mixture. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hamburger 'n' fixings sandwiches
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Meanwhile, toast hard rolls.
Stir soup, ketchup, pickle, mustard and pepper into skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; heat through. Spoon about 1/2 cup of the beef mixture onto each roll bottom. Top with desired toppings; adjust roll tops.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrots and pineapplescreston, iowa
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sugar, butter, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until clear and thick.
Add pineapple and carrots.
Heat and serve at once.

title: bartow county puddin
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in uncooked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Simmer 2 hours and drain.
Make syrup and bring to a boil.

title: lamajeun(armenian pizza)
directions: Roll out each biscuit the size of saucer on floured board.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Top each biscuit with meat mixture and spread evenly.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until done.
Makes 30.

title: danish pineapple cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and the pineapple; let stand.
Mix warm milk, water, dry yeast and sugar and set aside. Mix the margarine, flour, salt and the egg yolks.
Add the yeast mixture and mix well.
Divide the dough into two parts.
May have to add more flour until pliable consistency.
Roll for 18 x 12 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread dough in the pan until sides are covered.
Pour the cream cheese mixture into the dough and roll the second part of the dough the same as the first, covering the top like a pie.
Brush top of dough with the beaten egg whites and top with granulated sugar and ground nuts.
Let rise for 1/2 to 1 hour until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: california rice dish
directions: Brown beef with onion and drain off fat.
Stir in water, rice, bouillon cubes and dry mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed, approximately 25 minutes.
Stir in green pepper and tomato and sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes until cheese melts.

title: spicy carrot cake
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Measure ingredients in order listed into a large bowl, except carrots, nuts and raisins.
Blend 1 minute at low speed and 2 minutes at high speed.
Stir carrots, nuts and raisins into batter.
Pour into greased 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or top with whipped cream and drizzle of honey, if desired.

title: vanilla pudding(also for pies.)
directions: Stir sugar and flour together.
Add egg yolks and stir.
Add milk slowly.
Cook on medium heat until bubbles and thickens.
Cook until smooth.
Add vanilla; cool.

title: collector's cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch or 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for 8-inch layers; 30 to 35 minutes for 9-inch layers or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely; frost.

title: chewy bar
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan with melted butter.
Sprinkle graham crackers on top of butter.
Sprinkle nuts over this. Sprinkle butterscotch and chocolate chips on top of this.
Cover with coconut and pour Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken in orange-almond sauce
directions: Season chicken with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Brown lightly in butter.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, cinnamon, ginger and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add to drippings in skillet.
Make a smooth paste.
Stir in orange juice, almonds and raisins.
Stir until thickened and boiling.
Pour over chicken and bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 450°.
Then bake, uncovered, 10 minutes more. Makes 4 servings.

title: two-step pound cake
directions: Place flour, sugar, butter, milk, eggs and vanilla (in that order) in a 4-quart bowl. Beat at low speed with a heavy-duty electric mixer for 1 minute, stopping to scrape down sides. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: hearty turkey stew
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut turkey into 1/2-inch thick slices. Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat until oil sizzles.
Put turkey, potatoes, carrots, onion and garlic in pan and cook and stir until turkey is no longer pink (about 10 minutes).
Sprinkle flour over mixture, cook and stir 1 minute; stir in chicken broth, wine, thyme and pepper; bring to a boil and add mushrooms.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 50 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Stir in parsley.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice about 6 big cooking apples.
Sift sugar, salt, flour and cinnamon over the slices.
Mix and place in a greased baking dish.

title: english apple pie
directions: Beat egg well and add all the rest of the ingredients in the order given.
Batter should be smooth and mixed well before stirring in apples and nuts.
Turn into a buttered pie pan.
(No crust in this pie.)
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
After it is cooled, cut in pieces or wedges and serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: coconut pecan impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two 8 or 9-inch greased and floured pie pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until light golden brown.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Put in greased jellyroll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine 2/3 can mushroom soup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish, then set it aside.
Beat egg; add bread crumbs, onion, salt and pepper and remaining mushroom soup.
Mix beef into it.
Shape into patties; brown on low heat until slightly brown. Mix Golden mushroom soup, beef broth and horseradish; mix together.
Place patties in cake pan.
Pour soup mix over it; bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Thicken gravy.
Ready to serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour 3/4 cups hot water over dates.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Add dates and water, flour, baking soda, salt, vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: tea sandwiches
directions: Slice bread.
Combine cream cheese, mayo and pineapple. Spread mixture on bread.
Garnish with cherries.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Remove green rind
and
red
pulp from watermelon rind. Cut rind (white
part)
into
even
one-inch
square
pieces. Combine lime in
water
to
cover
rind.
Let stand overnight. Rinse thoroughly.
Soak rind
in alum and water to cover for 2 hours. Rinse thoroughly.
Cover rind with cold water and boil until slightly tender
when
pierced
with fork (about 25 minutes). Melt sugar in
cups
of
hot water.
Place rind and drained, chopped pineapple
in sugar water and cook until rind is transparent.
(Add boiling water if syrup becomes too thick during cooking.) Pack in hot sterile jars and seal.

title: batter(flour)
directions: Beat all ingredients together in a bowl until smooth.
A good batter for fish, onion rings or veggies.

title: cashaw pie
directions: Peel off green skin of cashaw.
Cut into small squares and place in boiling water. Lower flame and allow to simmer until tender.
Remove from flame and add butter, sugar, vanilla flavoring, nutmeg and flour.
Mix to desired consistency. Fold in coconut last.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti in 2-inch pieces.
Additional cheese optional. Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add next 10 ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: all bran muffins
directions: Mix together and set aside.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Shred lettuce and place in mixing bowl. Rinse shrimp in a strainer and place in mixing bowl.

title: company french toast
directions: In 9 x 13 pan, melt 1 stick margarine. Into margarine, stir brown sugar and cinnamon. Stir and spread all around pan. Layer 2 layers of white bread (2 thicknesses, 12 slices in all). Beat eggs and milk and pour over bread. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pepperoni balls
directions: Prepare roll mix according to package directions, but omit egg and use 1 cup water.
Dough does not need to rise.
Place a cheese cube on a pepperoni slice.
Pinch off a piece of dough and shape carefully around the meat and cheese, forming a ball.
Repeat until all ingredients are used up.
Fry in deep, hot oil for about 5 minutes, until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels and serve warm.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, Jell-O, cornstarch, salt and boiling water.
Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Cook until thick and clear.
Cool.
Pour over berries in the baked pie shell.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all together for about 15 to 20 minutes. Will last for months in refrigerator.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Melt chocolate slowly over low heat (approximately 100°).
Add egg yolks.
Whip cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar. Fold egg whites and whipped cream into chocolate mixture.
Line spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Add 1/3 of chocolate mixture. Add a layer of ladyfingers.
Add 1/3 of chocolate mixture.
Add another layer of ladyfingers.
Add remaining chocolate mixture. Refrigerate until firm.

title: apple cake with hot caramel sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop pecans finely.
Peel, core and chop apples to make 2 1/2 cups.
Pieces should be size of your thumbnail.

title: cabbage carrot salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and oil.
Heat and pour over cabbage salad mixture.
Mix well.
Salt to taste.
Makes a big dish.
I put it in jars and store in refrigerator for a long time.

title: brunch egg dish
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: velvet chocolate glaze
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate.
Blend in butter and syrup, then stir in powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onions, pepper and celery in frying pan.
In casserole dish, mix minute rice with cream of chicken soup.
Drain sausage and vegetables and stir into rice and soup mixture.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Drain all fruit well.
Mix fruit, marshmallows, sour cream and sugar in large bowl.
Chill one hour.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine in a small bowl.
Add salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into a large Ziploc bag.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture.
Seal top of bag and shake until all pieces are coated.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; stir in sugar, syrup and butter.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes or until filling is slightly firm.
Center of pie may look soft when pie is gently shaken, but will firm when cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and grate apples; add 1 cup sugar and let stand 20 minutes.
Blend all other ingredients together.
Beat 2 minutes. Bake in greased loaf pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with crescent rolls.
Firmly press perforations together. Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes and cut into squares and serve immediately.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Microwave in a large Pyrex mixing bowl, sugar, syrup and peanuts for 7 to 8 minutes on High.
Remove and stir after 4 minutes.
Cook for the other 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove and stir in margarine and vanilla.
Cook for 1 more minute and stir in baking soda.
Stir until foamy.
Pour and spread on buttered cookie sheet. Break into pieces after cooled.

title: cabbage cheddar chowder
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper and drain.
Add celery, cabbage and water.
Cover and cook until cabbage is tender.
Mix in blender the cheese soup and milk and add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until ready to serve (will stick).

title: acorn squash *
directions: Place cut squash with salt and margarine upside on flat baking dish in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Remove; turn over and mix all other ingredients.
Pour over squash and bake 25 more minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
In another bowl, combine milk and pudding mix; add whipped topping and blend well by hand.
Combine both bowls and set aside.
Process cookies in food processor until they look like potting soil.
Layer cookies and filling in a clean 8 1/2-inch flowerpot, starting and ending with cookies.
Wrap stems of artificial flowers in plastic wrap and insert.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: crock-pot brisket of beef sloppy joes
directions: Be careful in your selection; do not choose too young and get one that was reared in a good moral atmosphere.

Some insist in keeping them in a pickle while others keep them in hot water. Even poor varieties can be made sweet, tender and good when garnished with patience, sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses.
Then wrap them in understanding; keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
They keep for years, getting more mellow and sweet.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Heat cheese, butter, onion, water and soup in a saucepan.
Pour over other ingredients.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peppered cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Hidden Valley Ranch well.
Shape into ball.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, sprinkle Lawry's seasoned pepper all over.
Serve with crackers.

title: grits casserole
directions: Add grits to boiling water and cook as directed on box.
When grits are done, add sausage, raw eggs and grated cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into a loaf pan or baking dish with 1/2 stick melted butter inside.

title: eddy's coconut cream pie
directions: Mix together 2/3 cup sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour.
Beat egg yolks in separate bowl, gradually add milk.
Gradually add egg mixture to dry ingredients, beating well.
Cook and stir over boiling water until thick.
Add 1 cup coconut, butter and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into baked 9-inch pastry shell. Meanwhile, prepare meringue.

title: 7 layered salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite size.
Cover bottom of dish.
Mix mayonnaise with the sugar.
Layer the cheese on top of mayonnaise. Make the day before you eat it and refrigerate it.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add sausage, bread cubes and cheese; stir.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand few minutes before serving.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; dice.
Use enough chicken stock to moisten dressing mix.
Combine soups and sour cream.
Pour over the diced chicken you have placed in a casserole dish.
Top with moistened dressing.
Bake one hour at 300°.

title: sweet and sour hotdogs
directions: Cut hotdogs into bite size pieces.
Put hotdogs in skillet and brown in butter.
Stir in honey, jelly and mustard.
Stir until jelly melts and mixture becomes smooth.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Roll steak in flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until tender. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients and put as a seal over layered vegetables.
Refrigerate 24 hours and toss before serving.

title: carrot-pineapple-nut salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin, stirring until dissolved. Add sour cream and mayonnaise and blend well.
Chill mixture until it begins to thicken slightly, then stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into 2-quart mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Nice served on lettuce with additional nuts sprinkled on top.

title: sausage and pasta casserole
directions: Prepare ziti as directed and drain.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cook sausage meat on medium-high heat in saucepan until brown, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Ricotta, parsley, Parmesan, basil and 1 cup spaghetti sauce.
Add ziti and toss to coat well.
Spoon into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Pour 1 cup sauce over mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage until crumbly and drain well.
Add rice, soup, water, onion and celery and mix well.
Turn into 2-quart casserole dish.
(Do not add salt.)
Cover and bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Wrap 8 green beans in a bacon slice and place in a 9 X 13 baking dish. Arrange more bean bundles in the dish until all beans are used. Combine the margarine and brown sugar. Pour over bean bundles. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes.

title: brown 'n serve rolls(a crisco recipe)
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 2 cups flour and yeast.
In saucepan, heat milk, sugar, Crisco and salt until warm and Crisco is melted (115°).
Add to flour mixture; add egg.
Beat at low speed for 60 seconds, until combined.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour with spoon to make a soft dough.

title: clymer cucumber concoction
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl and marinate overnight. When ready to serve, pour off about 2/3 of the liquid.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Place sugar, shortening and salt in mixing bowl.
Pour in boiling water; mix well and let cool.
Add yeast and eggs.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
This may be set in refrigerator to make fresh hot rolls daily.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Preheat oven.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: apple muffins
directions: Beat the sugar and the eggs together.
Add the dry ingredients along with the salad oil and vanilla.
Stir in the grated apple, walnuts (chopped) and the raisins.
Pour into greased muffin tins or paper cups.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: fish filet parmesan
directions: Wash and pat fillet dry with paper towels.
Arrange in greased baking pan. Sprinkle salt and pepper over fish.
Mix sour cream with cheese, chives and crumbs.
Spread over fish.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes per inch of thickness. Garnish with watercress.
One-half-inch thick- cook 5 minutes. One-inch thick - cook 10 minutes.
One and one-half-inch thick - cook 15 minutes.
Measure thickness by measuring thickest point of fillet.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients.
Add cucumbers and onion.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, brown and white sugar and peanut butter together.
Add the eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add salt to the flour and add to first mixture.
Stir in the chocolate chips. Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet or spray with Pam.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, egg, milk and extracts in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions, set aside to cool.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Pour over cabbage when needed.
This keeps in the refrigerator for weeks.

title: rebecca's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash.
Drain well.
Add to onion which has been sauteed in 1 tablespoon Mazola margarine (do not brown).
Add chopped or mashed up eggs to soup.
Add Beau Monde.
Mix thoroughly with squash.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Add crumbs.
Put squash mixture in casserole dish and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumb topping is golden color.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Melt together on low heat (double boiler).
Remove from heat. Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix in 4 to 6 teaspoons hot water, one at a time.
Spoon onto No Fry Doughnuts.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Melt butter; add flour and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Work together well.
Spread over bottom of large Pyrex dish, 13 x 9-inches.
Bake at 325° until very lightly brown.

title: chik divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Heat soup and add cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice; stir until cheese melts.
Add chik (Fri Chik or chicken) and broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with stuffing mixed according to package.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Place juices, sugar, spices and water in a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over tea.
Let steep for 3 hours.
Strain into jars and refrigerate.
At serving time add this mixture to enough boiling water to make 1 gallon of liquid.
Serves 30.

title: chipped beef and onion dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and soup.
Blend in chopped dried beef and onions.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Stir together cornmeal, flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine cereal and milk.
Let stand 2 minutes or until cereal is slightly softened.
Add egg whites, oil, corn, cheese and green onions.
Add flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Spread batter into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° about 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: gram's quick casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes about 10 minutes; drain.
Chunk the chicken up; peel baby onions.
Add all together in casserole dish.
Slice butter all around in dish.
Sprinkle paprika all over the whole dish.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: four layer tortillas
directions: In iron skillet, braise the onion and green chilies (drained) and remove from heat.
Cook ground chuck and add 1/2 jar salsa just before meat is done; save the other half.

title: cole slaw with ramen noodles
directions: Heat oil.
Lightly brown almonds, sesame seed and Ramen noodles.
Set aside.
Thinly shred cabbage.
Chop fine the green onions and green pepper.
Combine all together.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish: 1/3 sauce, 1/2 noodles (4 or 5 noodles), 1/2 meat (raw), 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/3 sauce, 1/2 noodles, Cheddar cheese, 1/2 meat, 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/3 sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, covered. Uncover and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Let set
for 15 minutes before serving.

title: fish chowder
directions: Boil 2 cups water and add the fish.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Remove fish and save the liquid.
Saute onion in butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Heat until bubbly, then add fish liquid and 1/2 cup water.
Add potatoes and simmer, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Stir in the fish and milk.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: teriyaki-style chicken
directions: Mix and whip the ingredients except chicken.
Flatten chicken breast; marinate in sauce several hours or overnight.
Broil, adding some marinade.

title: bagna caulda
directions: In a small saucepan, heat butter, olive oil and garlic.
Keep warm over very low heat for 5 minutes.
Add anchovies.
Increase heat until mixture begins to simmer.
Do not boil.
Stir until anchovies have disintegrated.
Add 2 tablespoons of sour cream before serving.
Transfer to a small flameproof bowl.
Stir in parsley (optional).
Use any fresh vegetables for dipping.

title: quick pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin or fruit of choice. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients along with water to cream mixture.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add 4 chops.
Brown both sides over medium heat.
Repeat with remaining chops.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt in microwave: Pet milk, oleo and chocolate chips.
Mix dry ingredients: flour, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs and add to milk mixture.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla flavoring. Prebake a pie crust for 3 minutes.
Place pecans in the bottom of shell.
Pour chocolate mixture over pecans and bake 20 minutes at 350° or until a crack is seen on top 1-inch from the edge.
Top will be a lighter brown.

title: banana-pineapple cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir together.
Do not beat.
Pour into a greased 9-inch tube pan and bake about 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
(It is important that cake is real cool or it will stick to bottom of pan.)

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Line 9 x 13 glass dish with graham crackers.
Mix Cool Whip and pudding according to directions. Layer 1/2 of this mixture on top of crackers. Layer again with crackers and again with remaining pudding mixture.
End with third layer of crackers. Spread frosting on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheesy meat loaf with mashed potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ground beef, bread, egg, ketchup, salt, pepper and onion.
Put into round or 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and water chestnuts.
Mix with chopped celery and chopped onion.
Add grated cheese and mayonnaise; toss.
Mix together Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Put in casserole dish and top with crackers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened (do not beat).
Stir in bananas, pineapple, vanilla and 1 cup pecans and spoon batter into 3 greased and floured pans (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 or 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers, top and sides.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Frost with "Cream Cheese Frosting."

title: twisted lemonade
directions: Fill a 14 oz. glass with ice. Add vodka and triple sec. Top off with sweet and sour mix. Serve with a straw.

title: quiche
directions: Brown pie shell in 350° oven for 5 minutes. Peel and slice tomatoes. Salt and pepper and dip in flour.

Saut in oil. Remove and drain. Place tomatoes and onions in bottom of pie crust; place Provolone cheese. Mix cream and eggs together. Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle Swiss cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza beans
directions: Drain and rinse beans; place in slow cooker or Dutch oven. In a skillet, brown sausage, breaking into small pieces.
Add sausage to beans.
Add a little oil to sausage fat and saute onion and green pepper in it.
Add sauteed vegetables, olives, tomatoes, salt, oregano, basil and garlic to cooker or oven.
Break up tomatoes with spoon; mix ingredients well.
If using slow cooker, cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours.
In Dutch oven, cook 2 to 3 hours to blend flavors.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder and add to beaten eggs and creamed mixture.
Add rolled oats, nuts and gumdrops.

title: copper pennies or marinated carrots
directions: Mix all and marinate overnight.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the sugar, margarine and Crisco. Add flour alternately with butter to which soda and vanilla have been added. Add lightly beaten egg yolks. Fold in beaten egg whites, coconut and nuts. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Use a Bundt pan.

title: refreshing slush
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients until dissolved, then add the water and juice.
Mix well and freeze in large bowls or two 12 x 9-inch cake pans.

title: oh so chocolate balls
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate chips,
Remove from heat. Add sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and walnuts.
Mix well. Cool in refrigerator 10 minutes.
When mixture will form a loose ball, roll 1-inch size balls in individual toppings.
Keep refrigerated.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, sour cream
and
onion
soup mix in a bowl.
Pour over chicken. Top with
almonds.
Bake, covered tightly 1 1/2 hours.
Bake 15 minutes uncovered.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mommy's lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in yogurt and then crackers.
Place in glass baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Do not overlap (it's okay to crowd them).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not turn.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil in a large saucepan.
Food coloring may be added to color the dough.
Stir over medium heat until mixture leaves the sides of the pan and forms a ball; add oil.
Knead gently, working oil into the dough.
Store in an airtight container.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a saucepan, cook pudding and milk over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from the heat and cool slightly. Meanwhile, in a bowl, cut peanut butter into confectioners sugar until small crumbs form.
Peanut butter consistency may vary; add additional confectioners sugar, if necessary.
Set aside about 2 tablespoons of crumbs; sprinkle remaining mixture into pie shell. Pour pudding over crumbs.
Chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.

title: quick pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Bake in pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna; drain and blend with soups and Parmesan cheese, sour cream, onion, olives, pimentos and garlic salt.
Stir in turkey; spread 1/4 turkey mixture in 9 x 13 pan.
Alternate layers of lasagna, turkey and American cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes; cut and serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together. Spread in a 9 x 13 inch pan which has been greased and floured.
For a thin cookie type dessert spread on a larger cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.
1/2 recipe bakes well in a 9 x 9 inch pan.

title: date pinwheels(cookies)
directions: Cook together the first 3 ingredients.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Let cool and add the pecans.
In another bowl, mix well the remaining ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours. Take out and divide in 4 equal parts. Roll dough out on floured board and spread each portion with 1/4 of the filling.
Roll up like a jelly roll. Store in refrigerator overnight. Slice and bake at 410° until golden brown. Rolls may be kept in freezer to slice and bake as needed.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 275°. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. Combine shortening, sugars, vanilla and water. Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs. Add flour mixture; mix well. Stir in 1 package of chocolate morsels. Drop by 1/2 teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 275° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 100 (2-inch) cookies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together until smooth.
Put in crust.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: pistachio-coconut surprise
directions: Combine sour cream and pudding mix.
Add coconut and pineapple; stir until blended.
Spoon into loaf pan and freeze until firm.
Dip pan in warm water and unmold onto serving plate. Makes 6 servings.

title: fruitcake
directions: Cream sugar with butter until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well. Beat in molasses.
Combine 1 cup flour, baking soda and spices and add to the creamed mixture alternately with the brandy beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Combine raisins, walnuts, fruit mix and dates; toss with 1 cup flour to coat well and then stir into batter.
Place dough into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans lined with wax paper.
Bake at 225° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours. Place shallow pan of boiling water on the bottom of oven during baking but remove it the last 30 minutes of baking.
Cool in pans on a rack.
Remove cake and peel off wax paper.
Wrap in foil. Store in cool place.
Will keep months in the refrigerator.
Makes 2 cakes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add slightly beaten eggs and all other ingredients to corn. Pour into casserole and bake at 400° until firmly set, about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions using 3 cups cold milk; fold in Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Arrange a layer of wafers on bottom of a 2-quart round baking dish or bowl. Spread 1/4 pudding over wafers; top with banana slices.
Continue layering wafers, pudding mixture and bananas, ending with pudding. Cover and chill.
Easy and delicious!

title: cherry chicken
directions: In skillet brown chicken in margarine for 10 minutes on each side.
Season with a little salt and pepper.
Drain off excess margarine.
Combine pie filling, wine, orange juice, brown sugar, salt and spices.
Pour over browned chicken.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix ingredients and spread a little on bottom of pan.
Place tortillas on mixture and put a large amount of sauce on tortilla and roll.
Tortillas may need to be warmed so they won't crack. Save enough sauce to spread over top.

title: caramels
directions: Place sugar, syrup and salt in a 3-quart heavy saucepan; cook over medium-high heat until mixture reaches firm ball stage (244°), stirring as needed. Add butter and stir while it melts. Slowly add milk, keeping mixture boiling.
Cook rapidly and stir constantly until mixture reaches firm ball stage again.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, then pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Makes 81 caramels (1 x 1-inch).

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix sugar and margarine; add egg, water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour.
You may add another egg or more flour to get desired consistency, then add chocolate chips and spoon out on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: oven-fried pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops and set aside.
Combine egg white and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Combine breadcrumbs, Italian seasoning, paprika and dash of garlic powder; stir well.
Dip chops in egg white mixture; dredge in breadcrumb mixture.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together with desired amount of mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Salt and pepper.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cover the dates with the boiling water and to this, add butter, salt and sugar. Slowly add dry ingredients (flour and baking soda), then add the nuts, egg and vanilla. Use 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/4 x 2 1/2-inch foil loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine butter, bourbon, and milk.
Add sugar and knead until mixture is blended and does not stick to hands.
Knead in pecans. Refrigrerate one hour.
Shape into one inch balls.
Freeze.

title: oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Stir in vanilla and egg and beat until smooth and creamy.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Fold flour mixture into creamy mixture and stir until smooth.
Last, fold in rolled oats and nutmeats until evenly distributed.
Form into roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake in 350°
oven 10 to 12 minutes.
I usually double the recipe.

title: divinity candy
directions: Use 1 (2-quart) and 1 (1-quart) heavy pans and a candy thermometer.
In the large pan, put 3 cups sugar, white corn syrup and 1 cup water.
Let boil to 260° (hard ball stage).
In the small pan, put 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Let boil to 238° (soft ball stage).
Start cooking larger pan first.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat, stirring to separate, until cooked.
Add soups and mix well.
Place in a glass baking dish.
Cover with cheese, then with Tots.
Place in a 350° oven until cheese melts and Tots are brown.

title: corn dogs
directions: You will need deep fat fry oil.

title: mexi-corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Mix corn, soup and cheese.
Add rice and oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add some grated cheese on top.

title: chocolate lovers dream
directions: Crush enough Oreos to line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Fold in Cool Whip and candy bar pieces.
Spread on top of Oreos.
Line rim of pan with remaining Oreos.
Garnish with bits of cookies.
Put in fridge. Serve cold.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Prepare the cake per the directions on the cake in a 13 x 9-inch (1/4 sheet) pan.
Leave the cake in the pan when it is baked.
Poke holes in the top of the cake with a wooden spoon handle.
Pour the condensed milk (not evaporated milk) over the cake, followed by the caramel topping.
Top the cake with Cool Whip and sprinkle with the crushed Heath bar candy bars. Refrigerate before serving for at least 1 hour.

title: orange glazed yams
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until almost done.
Arrange in baking dish.
Cook sugar, orange juice and cornstarch 5 minutes.
Add butter or margarine.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients in order listed.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: country style steak
directions: Brown seasoned meat in 2 tablespoons oil, using an iron skillet.
Remove steak from skillet and make brown onion gravy by adding onion to 1/4 cup melted shortening.
Saute onion until brown.
Add flour and blend, stirring until brown.
Add water, stirring constantly, until thickened, then put meat into gravy. Cover with an iron lid and simmer for 1 hour.
The process of steaming will make the steak very tender.
Serves 6.

title: christmas bread
directions: Crumble yeast into 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Stir.
Heat milk until a film shines on top.
Stir in margarine and sugar into milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast and beaten eggs.

title: candy kiss cookies
directions: Cream together peanut butter and milk.
Add Bisquick and vanilla.
Roll in balls and sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Place kiss on each as soon as removed from oven.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk and Worcestershire sauce; mix thoroughly.
Flake crabmeat and add to cheese mixture along with onions.
Turn into greased 8-inch pie pan.
Top with almonds.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until heated through.
Serve with crackers.

title: mushroom caps
directions: Clean and de-stem mushrooms.
Fill mushrooms with sausage. Place mushrooms on cookie sheet, caps down.
Bake at 275° for 50 minutes.
Mix tomato sauce, white wine and oregano together in slow cooker.
Simmer while mushrooms are baking.
Add mushrooms to sauce and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour, salt and soda together. Add well beaten eggs to first mixture, then add dry ingredients. Mash bananas fine with fork.
Mix bananas and nuts to mixture. Bake a loaf 30 minutes at 325° to 350° until crust is dark brown and doesn't stick to toothpick when inserted to center.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook wide noodles; drain.
Put in mixing bowl.
Add can of tuna, broccoli and cauliflower mix and can of cream of mushroom soup; mix well.
Put in casserole dish; top with crushed potato chips.
Bake until thoroughly heated at 350°.

title: portofino mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in undrained pineapple, cranberry sauce and wine.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into 2-quart serving bowl and chill until firm.
When mixture is set, soften cheese and gradually beat in sour cream.
Spread over Jell-O and chill. Serves 8.

title: southern fried chicken and brown cream gravy
directions: Shake moist pieces of chicken, a few pieces at a time, in a paper bag with 1/2 cup flour, salt and pepper until thoroughly coated.
Put oil in a large skillet.
When oil is hot, put in chicken; cover and brown quickly on both sides.
Reduce heat. Cook about 25 minutes.
Remove cover and continue cooking about 10 minutes.
Remove and drain chicken on paper towel.
Drain oil, leaving 2 tablespoons in skillet.
Add remaining flour and brown. Gradually add the water, stirring constantly until creamy and thick.
Serve over biscuits or cornbread.

title: eclairs
directions: For pudding mixture, mix together the pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour half the pudding mixture over crackers.
Lay another layer of crackers; top with remaining pudding.
Top with another layer of crackers.

title: fudge chewies
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 c. Sago milk; set aside.
Mix cake mix with 1/3 c. Sago milk and margarine.
Put half of cake mixture in greased 9 X 13 pan and bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and add in order chocolate chips, melted caramel mixture, nuts and remaining half cake mixture.
Last half of cake mixture will be very thick; drop by spoonfuls on nuts.
Bake 20 minutes more. Cool and cut into bars.

title: map modeling 1
directions: Mix salt and flour in a bowl.
Add enough water until like thick frosting.
Stir.
Add food coloring before molding or mold and paint when dry. Draw map on heavy cardboard.
Spread mixture on cardboard, adding hills and valleys.
Dry.
Paint, if desired.

title: classic lasagne
directions: In heavy large pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes (put through blender or cut with edge of spoon), paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano. Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken thighs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Simmer chicken thighs in butter in a large frying pan for 10 to 12 minutes until somewhat browned.
Add cooking wine; keep cooking about 5 minutes more.
Remove chicken to baking pan, skin side up, in a single layer (don't stack).

title: meaty vegetable chili
directions: In a large Dutch Oven, brown the beef and chicken in oil over med-hi heat.
Drain and add: water, carrots, zucchini, tomatoes, onions, turnip, and green or red pepper; bring it to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer for 1 hour, or until the beef is tender.
Add the beans and chili sauce; simmer for 15 minutes longer.
Yeilds 16 servings or 4 quarts.

title: fluffy banana pudding
directions: Put pudding and cold milk in a large bowl with cover.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and add Cool Whip, banana extract and bananas.
Mix gently.
Vanilla wafers can be added to mixture but I prefer to serve on the side so vanilla wafers are crisp, not soggy.
Store in refrigerator.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach
in
water.
Drain
and squeeze out excess water. Add sour cream, soup mix and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 to
30 minutes,
until
lightly browned.
Serves 8.
"Even spinach haters love this!"

title: onion dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender for 20 seconds, until creamy. Stir in 1 teaspoon celery seed.
Yields 1 1/2 pints.

title: date finger balls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients on medium heat.
Take off heat.
Combine with remaining ingredients, then form in balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 2 medium loaf pans.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and poppy seed. In another bowl, combine oil, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add this to dry mixture and mix well.
Divide between the pans and bake for 50 minutes.

title: stain glass candy
directions: Melt chocolate and butter (cool). Add nuts and marshmallows. Shape into 2 rolls 2 1/2 inch in diameter. Roll on wax paper. Refrigerate until chilled. Slice in thick slices.

title: sauerbraten
directions: In 3 or 4-quart casserole, combine all ingredients, except brown sugar and gingersnaps and marinate in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days.
Remove meat from marinade and strain marinade.
Place meat and strained marinade in Dutch oven and simmer meat on stove burner until tender, about 1 hour.
Return meat to casserole and strain cooked liquid.
Place strained liquid in Dutch oven with sugar and gingersnaps and heat until mixture thickens.
(Add more gingersnaps if needed for thickness.)
Pour gravy mixture over meat in casserole and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with hot potato salad, red cabbage, sauerkraut salad and black bread.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Meanwhile, soften the yeast in the water.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before pouring into mixture of sugar, shortening, salt and 1/2 cup of the flour which has been blended with the scalded milk.
Add about half of the remaining flour to the yeast mixture and beat until very smooth.
Beat in egg, then add enough of the flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
(If this is to be used for hot cross buns, sift 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon allspice with flour.
Stir in 1 cup currants and 3 ounces of chopped candied citron.)
Knead until the dough is smooth and elastic.

title: raspberry creme dessert
directions: Mix raspberries, partly thawed, with 2 tablespoons cornstarch that has been moistened with 1 tablespoon cold water.
Place over low heat and cook until thick, stirring constantly (let cool).

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Mix all of this together and put in container that you can cut in and freeze.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Melt butter; add carrots and onions.
Saute 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in flour, then broth, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Bring to boil, simmer about 15 minutes until carrots are tender.
Cool slightly.
Puree in blender until smooth.
Stir in half and half.
Serve either cold or hot.
Garnish with parsley if hot or cucumber slices, if chilled.

title: date balls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add dates; cook for 12 to 15 minutes.
Then add Rice Krispies, vanilla and nuts.
Let cool, then roll into balls and roll balls in confectioners sugar.

title: country fried steak
directions: Cut round steak into pieces.
Put salt, pepper and garlic with flour on both sides.
Fry in a covered skillet over medium heat until almost done.
Remove meat; pour oil from pan and add soup and 1 can water.
Put meat back and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken a la king(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, melt butter on High for 1 minute.
Blend in flour. Add milk and broth and mix with whisk. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes. Stir with whisk after 4 minutes.
Mix in chicken and veggies.
Microwave on High 7 to 10 minutes. Serve over biscuits or toast.

title: flavorful tofu(kids will eat)
directions: Cut tofu into 1/2-inch thick slices and allow to dry on paper towels.
Start to cook brown rice.
In large saute pan saute onions in olive oil until translucent.
Add mushrooms, red wine and spices and continue to cook until mushrooms are soft.
Coat tofu with wheat germ by placing wheat germ in shallow dish and gently pressing tofu.
Add tofu to saute, moving vegies aside to place tofu directly on pan.
Pour can of tomatoes over all and gently mix vegies onto top and in with the tomatoes.
Allow to cook, covered, on medium heat for 7 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine with other ingredients.
Add flour.
Let rise to double bulk, in warm place.
Stir down.
Turn into greased pan and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Lightly brown in margarine and remove from pan.
Saute onion.
Stir in flour and seasonings. Stir in broth and cook until thickened.
Stir in beef, yogurt or sour cream.
Do not boil.
Serve with noodles.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onion, and green pepper.
Put in everything else and let simmer 30-45 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Layer in baking pan with sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20-30 minutes at 300-350°.

title: three corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly brush a shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole with some butter.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix with soups, mushrooms and tomatoes. Line casserole dish with crushed Doritos.
Fill with beef mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: grilled italian chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Refrigerate until ready to grill.
Baste with mixture.
Grill until done.

title: haystacks
directions: Place morsels (1/2 bag at a time) in hot double boiler.
Stir until all morsels are somewhat melted.
Add chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Stir.
Dip out by the spoonful and place on wax paper to harden.
May place in freezer to harden faster, then eat.
May substitute chocolate morsels for butterscotch if desired.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix butter, mustard and poppy seed together with a fork to make a spread.
Split rolls top from bottom and spread mustard mixture evenly on both top and bottom half of each package of rolls.
Mix ham, cheese and onion together and spread on bottom half of each pan of rolls.
Replace top half of rolls and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 80 rolls.

title: texas hash
directions: Mix solid tomatoes, rice and spices in bowl.
Fry onions and bell pepper.
Add hamburger, then tomatoes, rice and spices.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes in baking dish.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve shortening in boiling water.
Add cold water, sugar, salt and beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to egg mixture.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well between additions.
Place in greased loaf pan; let rise until doubled. Bake at 425° until done.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave butter or oleo 1 1/2 minutes.
Add sugar and milk; mix and microwave 3 minutes.
Stir and microwave for 2 more minutes.
Stir and microwave 3 minutes.
Stir and microwave for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Stir and add nuts and vanilla.
Stir and pour into butter coated pan.
Let cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Mix milk and flour alternately, mixing well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in blueberries. Bake in muffin pan at 350° until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream
butter and sugar together until fluffy; add next 4 ingredients.
Line pie pan (8-inch) with pastry and sprinkle with pecan
halves; pour the filling over pecans.
Bake in hot oven, 425°,
for	10
minutes; reduce temperature to 325° and bake 35 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Makes
(8-inch) pie.
Place cover over pie when it is removed from oven.

title: easy smoked brisket
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Place in large baking pan and pour liquid smoke over it with a heavy hand.
A large brisket will take almost all of a 5 ounce bottle.
Cover tightly with foil and cook in a 275° oven all night.
remove foil, baste with juices and let stand.
It will be very tender and tasty.

title: gorp
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in jar and cover.
For small amount, use 1 cup of each ingredient.

title: texas tortilla soup
directions: Heat butter and oil in large kettle.
Saute onion, garlic, carrots and celery.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cumin, chili powder, salt, lemon pepper, Tabasco sauce and flour.
Add tomatoes and chicken broth.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add cooked chicken and heat thoroughly.

title: dutch oven chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken breasts as thin as possible; season with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Place ham and cheese in breast and roll up, securing with toothpicks if needed.
Dip each piece in butter and roll in cornflake crumbs.

title: pear bread
directions: Mix all together very well, except the pears.
Then stir in the mashed pears.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes and remove. Makes 1 loaf of bread.

title: anise cookies
directions: Use part of flour to flour anise seed.
Mix ingredients.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for about 15 minutes. Sugar tops before baking.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Clean and slice strawberries.
Put in bowl and add sugar; set aside until sugar dissolves.
Cut cake in half in middle making 2 layers.
Take half the juice from strawberry mixture and pour into holes made by fork to penetrate through cake layer.
Place half the glaze on cake and half the strawberries.
Place cake layer on top and repeat with remaining juice, glaze and strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: "bing cherry salad"
directions: Let cream cheese warm up at room temperature.
Then add milk and mash together with fork.
Make jello.
Add cream cheese mixture to jello.
Add cherries and nuts last.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate until set.

title: overnight salad
directions: Drain peas, green beans and pimento.
Add onion and pepper.

title: not so sweet pecan pie
directions: Soften butter and cream.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add syrup and salt.
Beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pie shell, and bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: crazy crust peach cobbler
directions: Place butter in baking dish to melt.
Combine flour, baking powder, sugar, milk and beat.
Pour batter over melted butter; do not stir.
Place fruit evenly on batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.
Pastry rises to top.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first eight ingredients.
Add pork and mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place in a 15 in. x 10 in. x 1 in. baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Remove from the oven; drain on paper towels.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine hush puppies mix, milk and eggs, mixing well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in corn.
Drop level tablespoonfuls into 375° oil.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Makes 24.

title: chunky chili(must be prepared 1 day in advance)
directions: Heat oil in a heavy
4-quart pan over medium heat.
Add beef, stirring frequently with
a
wooden
spoon
until
meat changes color but does not
burn.
Lower
heat
and
stir
in garlic. Combine chili powder, cumin and flour.
Sprinkle meat with chili mixture, stirring
until
meat
is
evenly
coated. Crumble oregano over meat.
Add broth and stir until liquid is well blended.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Cool thoroughly. Cover and
refrigerate
overnight.
Reheat
chili slowly. Add beans.
Place cooked
rice
in
individual
serving bowls. Spoon chili mixture over rice.
Add 1 tablespoon sour cream to each serving.
Garnish with
lime
wedges to squeeze over each portion. Serves 8 to 10.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook fettucini according to package directions; drain well. Place in warm serving dish large enough for tossing.
Add butter, cream, Parmesan cheese and parsley; toss until fettucini is well coated.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry surprise french toast(makes 4 servings)
directions: Make a pocket in each bread.
Slice, cutting almost in half lengthwise.
Fill each with about 2 teaspoons strawberry spread. Place slices flat in a 9-inch pie pan.
In small bowl, beat together eggs and milk; pour evenly over bread.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
To serve, heat oil in skillet and fry slices 3 minutes on each side until golden brown.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reheats well in microwave by the piece. Enjoyed by Nina Vergari.

title: mom's 3 layer carrot cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add remaining 3 ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Use 3 pans, slightly greased.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large container.
Chill.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Whole hominy is made from the whole dried kernel of corn with the hull on and the germ removed.
The kernels may be white or yellow, depending on the type of corn.
Mr.
Loyal's daughters, Mary and Dot, often watched their father make hominy when they lived in Georgia.
He soaked the corn kernels in baking soda instead of wood-ash lye, a process that took a little longer, but which was safer.
Then he washed the kernels several times to remove the remaining hulls and germs.
Today, Mr. Loyal purchases his hominy in cans to make this dish.

title: donna g's favorite applesauce meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and place in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake 90 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: grilled turkey breast
directions: *Turkey is much easier to slice if partially frozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick with milk.
Fry and drain sausage.
Mix cheese and sausage into mix and bake at 375° until brown, about 12 minutes.

title: hot lemon sauce
directions: Mix well all ingredients.

title: fried corn
directions: Fry bacon and save a little grease. Saut onions in grease or butter. Add drained corn and bacon to onions. Cook a couple of minutes to blend flavors.

title: butterflied shrimp rockefeller
directions: Melt margarine in 2 to 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add shallots, basil, pepper and fennel.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender.
Squeeze liquid from spinach.
Add to shallot mixture and stir until heated through, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Peel shrimp, leaving the tail shell on.
Butterfly shrimp (slit underside from tail to head almost through and flatten).
Arrange shrimp on a lightly oiled baking sheet.
Spoon about a tablespoon of spinach mixture on each shrimp.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. (At this point, shrimp can be covered and refrigerated for 1 day. Let stand at room temperature while preheating oven.)
Bake in 425° oven until surface of shrimp is completely white (tail will be coral pink), 5 to 6 minutes.
Makes 6 appetizer servings or 2 to 3 entrees.

title: 3 step lemon pie
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Mix well and then pour into a graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate and then serve.

title: noodle delight
directions: Heat soups and add cheese.
Simmer celery, green pepper and onion in unsalted water until barely tender.
Drain.
Add all ingredients to cheese sauce.
Season to taste.
Cook noodles in unsalted water or use garlic or onion salt.
Drain well, using cold water.

title: easy muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Yield: 6 muffins.

title: oven roasted peanuts
directions: Place peanuts in 1 layer deep in a shallow baking pan. Roast in a 350 degrees oven for 15 to 20 minutes for shelled and 20 to 25 minutes for in shell peanuts. Remove from heat just short of doneness desired as peanuts continue to cook as they cool.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef slightly in oil.
Add both cans of soup.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta shells according to directions.
Chop onion, tomatoes, cucumber and black olives.
Mix all in bowl.
Add mushrooms, 1/2 jar of seasoning and all dressing.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: pat's barbecue sauce
directions: Fry onions first, then add all remaining ingredients.
Let simmer until ready.
Cool before using.
Good on Chicken or added to canned beans.

title: oreo cookie ice cream
directions: Mix together; pour into freezer and fill the rest of the way with homogenized milk.
Freeze.

title: easy salad
directions: Should be mixed ahead and let stand in refrigerator for a few hours.

title: oreo cookie ice cream cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and mix with 1 stick melted margarine. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze for 30 minutes. Soften ice cream and spread over cookie layer; return to freezer for another 30 minutes (or longer). Bring milk, syrup and margarine to a boil, stirring constantly for approximately 2 minutes. Add vanilla to hot mixture and let cool completely. Pour cooled mixture over vanilla ice cream and freeze another 30 minutes. Spread Cool Whip on top. Chill and serve.

title: bette's tomato pie
directions: Mix milk and Bisquick; will be sticky.
Pat into 9 to 10-inch deep pie plate.
Layer with sliced tomatoes and spices.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese; put on top of tomatoes.
Sprinkle water with a little more basil or Italian seasoning.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey lattice pie
directions: In a sauce pan bring water, vegetables and bouillon to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 3-5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. In a small bowl combine cornstarch and milk until smooth. Add to vegetable mixture. Bring to a boil, cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened. Add turkey or chicken, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper. Pour into a greased 8 in. square baking dish. Unroll crescent roll dough and separate into two rectangles. Seals seams and perforations. Place long sides together to form a square. Pinch edges together to seal. Cut into eight strips. Make a lattice crust over top of mixture. Bake at 375 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Cut dry ingredients into shortening.
Mix together vinegar, egg and water.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Mix with pastry blender.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix. Put in casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° about 35 minutes. Remove from oven; top with French's onion rings and cook 8 to 10 minutes longer.

title: old time soft gingerbread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter, add the egg and then the sifted dry ingredients, alternating with the milk.
Beat up well. Bake in hot oven.

title: salmon and oranges
directions: Remove the skin from the salmon.
In the bottom of a pan, place enough orange slices to have under the salmon.
Lay the salmon on top and sprinkle it with the nutmeg.
Place the remaining slices of orange over the salmon.
Pour on the wine and orange juice and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes or until the salmon is cooked.
Remove the salmon from the pan and place on serving dish.

title: 3 minute delight poppy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the poppy seed and nuts until smooth.
Add the poppy seed filling and the nuts, beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour in
a 10 inch angel food pan.
DO NOT GREASE PAN!
Cool cake before removing from the pan.

title: stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles in water with beef bouillon cube.
In skillet, brown garlic, onion and ground beef.
Add flour, salt, paprika and mushrooms.
Add soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Add 1/4 cup noodle water, if needed.
Keep heat low.
Mix all together and serve.

title: baked pimento cheese
directions: Combine milk, water, margarine and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Trim bread and break into pieces in a large bowl.
Pour liquid mixture over bread and let sit for 15 minutes.
Grate cheese; mash pimientos and add to mixture.
Add well beaten egg yolks and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Best served warm.

title: double chocolate nugget cookies(makes 4 to 5 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Blend first three ingredients.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Can top cookies with pecan half or sprinkles or colored sugar. Bake for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.

title: tuna time saver
directions: Mix tuna with onions, pimiento, rice, and tabasco sauce. Mix in soup and water. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until cheese bubbles and browns.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine margarine, cocoa and water. Bring to rolling boil.
Let cool a few minutes, then add sugar, flour, soda, salt, eggs and buttermilk.
Beat well and pour in greased and floured 15 x 10-inch sheet pan.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
While cake is baking, combine margarine, milk and cocoa.
Bring to boil.
Remove from stove and add powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well.
Set aside and spread on bars while they are still warm.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together. Add the butter, working in with a fork. Add the milk to make a soft dough. Place on a floured board and toss lightly until the outer surface looks smooth. Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut with floured biscuit cutter. Place on a greased pan and bake in a hot oven (475°) for 12 minutes.

title: s'more pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine chocolate pieces, marshmallows and milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows are melted. Cool. Fold in 1 1/2 cups whipped whipping cream into chocolate mixture. Spread hot fudge into pie crust. Gently spoon filling on top of fudge. Refrigerate until firm. Top with remaining whipped cream and drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: crispy molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening, in 3 or 4-quart saucepan, over low heat. Remove from heat; let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift together the flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt; add to first mixture.
Mix well; chill.

title: candied yams
directions: Can use 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup white sugar.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Makes 6 cups.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix corn and egg.
Add to dry ingredients.
Heat cup of oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Drop by tablespoons into oil.
Fry about 2 minutes on each side.

title: pork and green beans over rice
directions: In a 4-quart sauce pot, saute onion and garlic in 1/4 cup oil, until soft.
Add pork and brown slowly.
Drain broth only from green beans into meat; add 4 to 5 cups water, tomatoes and tomato paste, stirring well.
Season to taste.
Bring to a boil again and cook on medium until meat is almost done.
Add green beans and continue to cook for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Broth will be thick, but pouring consistency.
Serve over rice on individual dishes.

title: chicken and long grain wild rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of baking dish.
Spread enclosed packet of herb mix and dry onion soup mix over rice.
Arrange chicken evenly on rice.
Mix the mushroom soup with 2 cans water; pour over chicken and rice.
Cover with foil; bake at 375° for 1 hour. Remove cover last 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Pour over salad.
Store unused portion in refrigerator.
Stores well.

title: vanilla giffolds
directions: Mix all together.
Form into small crescent shape.
Bake. While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pepperoni appetizer(microwave)
directions: Spread pepperoni slices on microwave-safe dish.
Top each slice with 1/4 of slice of American cheese.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds or until cheese melts.

title: beef pie
directions: Add seasonings and onion to ground beef; mix well.
Add broth and moisten.
Thicken slightly with 1 1/4 tablespoons flour.
Place in casserole dish and spread with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° until heated through and potatoes slightly brown.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 11 g, protein 20 g, fat 11 g, calories 20. One serving = 2 meat medium fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: For richer cookies, increase butter to 1 cup and add 1 egg yolk.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine ingredients and store in airtight container.
To serve, add 1 heaping tablespoon per cup of hot water.

title: hearty chicken soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo or butter.
Put all vegetables (onion too) and broth in pot and cook until done.
Add chicken, parsley, oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat.
Mix flour in milk (I use a jar and shake it).
Add to vegetables, etc.
Heat.
Serves about 6.

title: rice stuffed flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown onion and mushrooms in hot margarine.
Mix broth, milk, cornstarch and dill.
Add to onion and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and return to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in carrots and zucchini; let stand for 5 minutes.
Stuff fish with mixture and sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Bake fish over any remaining mixture for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and
bake
at
325° for 30 minutes. May use 1/2 of cheese as topping.

title: buttermilk scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut in butter until blended and crumbly.
Gently mix in wet ingredients and fruit.
(Use raisins, dates, apricots, prunes, etc., whatever you prefer.) Knead mixture a few times.
Divide mixture in half and place on greased cookie sheet.
Form circle about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick. Score lightly on top, 6 pieces each.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Keeps very well, wrapped.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon in large frypan until crisp.
Drain on paper towel and crumble.
Cook ground beef in bacon fat in frypan until no pink remains.
Add onions; saute until tender and drain.
Combine beef, onion, catsup, salt, bacon, sugar, mustard and vinegar in baking dish.
Stirring gently add all beans, drained, to baking dish. Sprinkle bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can cook on top of stove.
May be prepared the night before baking.

title: poor boy pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and pour in graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: mother-pastor's grill meal(summer treat)
directions: Cut heavy-duty aluminum foil into 4 separate squares.
Mix the steak seasoning with ground beef.
Roll out 4 large patties. On each piece of foil, put a patty, 4 parts carrot, 1 part bell pepper and 4 parts potato.
Fold foil, tucking at the top seam and ends.
Place on hot barbecue grill for 20 to 25 minutes, turning only once.
Makes a meal for 4.
Excellent for picnics and camping. Delicious.

title: instant oatmeal(microwave)
directions: You will need a microwave-safe bowl.

title: squash pie
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook rotini.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together mayo, water, vinegar and sugar until smooth.
Add rest of spices, onion and celery to dressing.
Pour over rotini and mix thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight.
Stir salad two or three times during refrigeration.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in crock-pot.
Cook sausage, pepper and onion together.
Drain off grease.
Mix with melted cheese.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and celery until beef is browned and onion and celery soft.
Add rice and tomatoes.
Cook with lid on at low temperature until rice is cooked (approximately 30 minutes).
Stir in seasonings.
You may need to add 1/2 cup water to help rice cook if tomatoes don't have much liquid.
Just before serving, cover with cheese slices so cheese melts over top.

title: chili cheese jubilee
directions: Brown ground beef in 8-inch square Pyrex dish for 4 minutes in microwave.
Stir every 30 seconds.
Drain fat.
Melt butter for 20 seconds.
Add onions and cook for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, chili seasoning mix and water.
Cook for 1 3/4 minutes.
Beat the eggs slightly, add the cream and mix well.
Add egg-cream mixture slowly to tomato-chili mixture, stirring constantly.
Place 1/2 package chips in bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 of beef, then add a layer of 1/2 of the Monterey Jack.
Cover with 1/2 sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with sour cream and sprinkle with grated Cheddar.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes in microwave oven.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: old testament cake
directions: Blend first three ingredients in a small bowl until light and fluffy.
In a separate bowl, beat the 6 Jeremiah yolks, then add Kings, Amos, Chronicles and Leviticus alternately with the Judges mixture.
Fold in Nahum, Numbers and Samuel, then also the 6 Jeremiah whites, beaten stiff.
Bake in a heavily greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 3/4 hours at 300°.

title: f r z's hot cheese spread
directions: Mix ingredients and place in small casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve as a spread for crackers.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Set aside 3/4 cup bread crumbs.
Combine all ingredients except oil.
Form eight patties, coating each side with reserved bread crumbs.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat.
Cook 4 patties for 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Add other tablespoon oil and cook remaining tuna cakes.
makes 4 to 6 servings.
Total time:
25 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and let stand for 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: meat and spinach lasagna
directions: Boil 5-quarts water.
Add noodles to oil and boiling water. Cook for 12 minutes.
Brown ground beef (drain fat from it).
Add spaghetti mix, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Add 1/2 cup water. Let simmer a few minutes.
Drain water from noodles.
Lay one layer of noodles, one layer of meat, one layer of cheese, spinach, etc., ending with one layer of noodles, then top with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: dandelion gravy
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Fry until lightly browned. Sprinkle with flour and fry until flour is browned.
Turn heat to low.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar to your taste.
Stir in cream.
Simmer until hot; do not boil.
Add sliced eggs; pour over dandelions or lettuce.
Serve over boiled potatoes or toast.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon juice, vanilla and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and top with pie filling. Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ham `n' cheese mashed taters
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: tortilla cheese pinwheels
directions: Combine cream cheese, onions, meat and mustard.
Blend until smooth.
Spread thin layer over tortillas.
Roll tortillas up (egg roll shape).
Chill.
Before serving slice into 1/4-inch slices. Serve with salsa.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let set overnight.
Scoop out large pumpernickel or rye bread (round loaf).
Fill hollowed out bread with dip.
Use as a vegetable or bread dip.

title: skillet onions
directions: Melt margarine in iron frypan. Place onion slices in a single layer in pan. Sprinkle with about 2 tablespoons brown sugar. Cover. Cook over low heat 10 minutes. Turn onions. Sprinkle with remaining sugar. Cook 5 minutes. Uncover and cook, basting with margarine-sugar mixture, 5 minutes longer or until tender.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add bread cubes; sprinkle generously with garlic salt.
Brown, then bake in 250° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad(gluten free recipe)
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O in hot water, then add softened gelatin, cranberry sauce, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Allow Jell-O to set in refrigerator for several hours or preferably overnight.

title: bible cake
directions: Season to taste 2 Chronicles 9:9.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and cinnamon and set aside.
Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Slowly stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour batter into a 10-inch greased and floured pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour in a lightly greased medium-size casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Top with your favorite type of cheese right before removing from oven.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix according to directions and press into pizza pan.
Bake until golden.
Mix remaining ingredients (except fruits) and put on cool crust.
Cut up fruits and layer on top.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients except catsup and peppers.
Mix well and pack bell pepper halves, rounding off tops.
Top with catsup and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cheese cake crusts
directions: Mix together and press into 9-inch spring-form pan buttered up sides as far as you can.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping cake.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Boil cabbage until almost tender.
Add ground beef to cabbage. Add vegetables.
Cook until tender.

title: caramel biscuit ring-a-round
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 12-cup fluted tube pan. In small saucepan, combine brown sugar, nuts, margarine and water; heat until margarine melts, stirring occasionally.

title: baked crispy chicken
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Dip in 1/2 cup Pet milk.
Roll in mixture of corn flakes, Accent, salt and pepper.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan lined with Reynolds Wrap.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until drumsticks are tender when pierced with fork.

title: big kitty's beef stew
directions: Start cooking first 6 ingredients together in stock pot, cook on medium heat about 1 hour.
Add a bunch of carrots, cook about 30 minutes.
Add 3 to 4 medium size turnips, cook about 30 minutes.
Add 3 to 4 medium size potatoes, more salt and pepper, if needed.
Cook until potatoes are done.

title: caribbean grilled chicken with citrus
directions: In a non-metallic bowl, stir together chicken broth, orange juice concentrate, vinegar, jerk seasoning, orange peel and garlic. Cover and chill half of the mixture for sauce.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
In a plastic bag set in a shallow dish, combine chicken and remaining orange mixture.
Close bag and chill for 2 to 24 hours, turning bag occasionally to distribute marinade.

title: crisp roasted potatoes
