directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In shallow baking pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients, except potatoes. Add potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly. Bake, stirring occasionally, 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cook sugar and syrup over low heat.
When it comes to a boil, mix in peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Put corn flakes in a large bowl and pour mixture over corn flakes.
Mix and shape into balls.
Makes a lot of balls, but will be gone in a short while because they are so good.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In mixer, combine sweet potatoes, brown sugar, seasonings and eggs, mixing thoroughly.
Slowly mix in milk, half and half and butter. Pour into pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool. Makes 8 servings.

title: old-fashioned lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans in a microsafe dish, covered, with 1/2 cup water on High power for about 4 minutes.
Drain.
Reserve liquid. In another microsafe dish, combine red onion, red pepper, green onion and reserved liquid from lima beans.
Cover and microwave on High power for 2 minutes.
Add lima beans.

title: fruit and pudding
directions: Bring to a boil the juice/water mixture and add the 2 packages of pudding and stir until thick.
Let cool and then add the pineapple and oranges.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator and then add sliced bananas when serving.

title: pineapple nut loaf
directions: Cream butter well.
Add sugar and cream it.
Add beaten eggs and add sifted dry ingredients with milk.
Add bananas, pineapple and chopped nuts.
Bake in loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sour cream spice drops
directions: Mix together until creamy the sugar, margarine, vanilla, eggs and sour cream.
Sift together the flour, nutmeg, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Add to the sour cream mixture, stirring well.
Stir raisins and currants into batter.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with knife. Bake at 350° to 375° for approximately 10 minutes.
Watch carefully; they burn easily.
Makes a soft cookie.

title: sage dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together except salt, pepper and sage. Mix very well. Put in roaster and bake at
350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours. Stir and taste often. Season with salt, pepper and sage to taste.

title: prize salad
directions: Soften plain gelatine in a few spoons of pineapple juice (or orange juice).
Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over Jell-O and softened gelatine; stir to dissolve.
Add 1 cup ice water (or 8 ice cubes).
Chill.
Fold in cranberry sauce (mashed up) and crushed pineapple, juice and all.

title: pride of iowa cookies(1987)
directions: Blend sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add vanilla, coconut, oatmeal and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon. Makes 5 dozen cookies.
Drop teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: slaw
directions: Shred in order.
Don't mix!
Sprinkle with sugar to cover the entire top.
Bring to a boil the other ingredients and pour over vegetables while hot.
Do not stir!
Refrigerate at least 4 hours. Mix.
Great for a cookout!
Saves in refrigerator for days!

title: broccoli "glop"
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into greased casserole dish. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar with oleo.
Add eggs.
Stir together flour with baking powder; add alternately with milk.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour in 1/2 of batter.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Spread 1/2 the crumb mixture on the batter, then rest of batter and rest of crumbs.
Over the top drizzle 1/2 cup melted butter. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and mix in everything except Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Put them on top.
Put in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, to melt cheese.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add orange juice (juice from pineapple can be used with orange juice to make 2 cups).
Add orange sections and pineapple.
Chill until set.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oats in boiling water.
While this cools, cream oleo, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Add oatmeal with flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour and salt. Set aside. Beat egg yolks, vanilla and melted butter. Add nuts and mix this with first mix. Bake in pie tin for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken in mushroom gravy
directions: Place the chicken breasts in the slow cooker. Season with salt and pepper. Mix the wine and the soup. Pour over the chicken. Add the mushrooms. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours.

title: fish soup(fiskesuppe)
directions: Poach fish in water with spices, then remove fish and in the fish stock, cook carrot, leek and celery until done.
Make soup with butter and flour; add fish stock and milk.
Beat egg yolks and cream.
While beating, pour fish stock over egg yolks; add flaked fish and vegetables and sprinkle with chives before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken escalopes
directions: Pat the chicken dry with paper towel.
Whisk the egg whites with a fork until they just begin to froth, but are still liquid. Brush all surfaces of the chicken with the egg whites.
Put bread crumbs on a plate and mix in the chopped sage.
Season with a little salt and black pepper.
Place the chicken, one at a time, into plate of bread crumbs and sage and carefully press this mixture onto the surface of the chicken.
Put the oil into a large shallow pan and gently fry the prepared chicken on each side for 5 minutes until they are lightly golden and tender (set them aside and keep warm).
Mix all remaining ingredients, except for the garnish, in a small bowl, whisking well to blend the yogurt and mayonnaise evenly.
Place the cooked chicken on a serving dish and spoon a little of the sauce over.
Serve garnished with the lemon slices and additional nuts.

title: cheesy garlic potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes; drain. Add sour cream, margarine, garlic and milk. Blend all with mixer until lumps are gone. Pour into large baking dish and put Cheddar cheese on top. Place in warm oven until cheese is melted. Serves about 15 people.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Place cream cheese, sugar, butter and milk in large saucepan. Mix together over low heat until all ingredients are blended; add beaten eggs.
Add egg mixture to cooked noodles and mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cinnamon and crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg pie
directions: With electric mixer, whip butter until smooth. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one. Add flour and sugar. Add milk last. Pour into prepared pie crust shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Heat sugar, butter and evaporated milk to full rolling boil in 3-quart heavy saucepan on medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil on medium heat until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching, about 4 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme until melted; stir in vanilla and walnuts. Spread immediately in buttered 9-inch pan. Cool at room temperature at least 4 hours; cut into squares. Store in airtight container. Makes about 3 pounds.

title: "sweet pea salad"
directions: Drain peas.
Dice celery, onion and tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Garnish with paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Very easy to make and delicious.
Serve after chilled for at least one hour.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend thoroughly.
Stir in mashed bananas. Stir flour and soda together and add alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla and fold in nuts, if desired.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Layer graham crackers in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of batter on top of crackers and repeat layers.
Top with graham crackers and spread on milk chocolate frosting.
Chill overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In top of double boiler, combine butter, flour, salt, sugar and grated onion. Make a paste of this mixture and cook for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add swiss cheese and sour cream. Mix with beans and put in casserole dish. Top with corn flakes that have been crumbled, dot with butter and bake at 350° for 20 - 25 minutes.

title: ebbie's peanut brittle
directions: Combine margarine and peanuts in 10 inch iron frying pan.
Cook until peanuts start popping.
Add sugar and syrup.
Cook until they pop again.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
Stir until it foams.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
(Cook on medium high heat.)

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: monkey biscuits
directions: Put cut biscuits, sugar and cinnamon in brown bag and shake until coated.
Layer pieces in angel food cake pan.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 gallon container.
Add enough water to make one gallon. Chill until ice flakes and forms in freezer.
Serve.

title: cucumber relish(canning recipe)
directions: Combine cucumber, onion and canning salt; let stand 1 hour and drain. Add remaining ingredients. Boil 15 minutes and put in can. Seal.

title: quick potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in bowl.
Sprinkle paprika and parsley flakes over top if desired.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream to the chocolate mixture.
Mix well.
Then add 1 cup boiling water and again mix well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes, then remove and cool.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
This cake is very moist and keeps well.

title: linebacker soup
directions: In large pot, combine potatoes, green onions, chopped onions and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Place potato mixture into a blender and add cream cheese; puree until smooth.
Add Tabasco and salt.
Return soup to the pot to reheat.
Add the cooked, sliced sausage and stir until the soup is hot.
Serve hot with paprika sprinkled on top.
Serves 8.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Put in large pan buttermilk; add soda.
Let stand 3 minutes. Add sugar and butter.
Cook at a rolling boil, stirring constantly, until it will form a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Let cool to room temperature.
Beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: rice yummy
directions: Boil all
together
except rice; add rice.
Remove from heat and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: waldorf astoria pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add salt water and mix until flour is mixed and easy to handle.
Roll out as for pie crust.

title: pluck-it-bread
directions: Tear each biscuit apart in 2 pieces. Roll each half into balls, then roll each ball into butter, then in the brown sugar, cinnamon mixture, then in pecans. Place in a Bundt pan. Pour remaining leftover ingredients on top and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and 1 package of beef and combine with spices and cream cheese.
Line a plastic bowl with waxed paper or Saran Wrap; mold cream cheese mixture or roll into a log and wrap beef around cheese.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: tomato-cucumber salad
directions: To Make Dressing: Whisk together yogurt, lemon juice, parsley, Italian dressing, garlic and pepper until blended well.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then add the next 2 ingredients.
Pour into Bundt pan; bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut pecan brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch pan. In a large
bowl,
combine
brownie
mix, water, oil and egg. Beat 50 strokes
by
hand.
Add frosting and sour cream; mix well. Spread
batter in greased pan.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips evenly over
top.
Bake
at
350° for 42 to 52 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese; mix thoroughly.
Add pineapple and oranges; fold in whipped topping.

title: coffee chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toast almonds on baking sheet in oven until golden, about 10 minutes.
Dissolve coffee powder in 2 tablespoons hot water.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
With mixer at medium speed; beat sugar and butter until creamy.
Beat in cooled coffee, vanilla and eggs.
Beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake until edges turn brown, about 3 minutes.

title: lo-cal chili
directions: Combine and cook until thick.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: In a small bowl, lightly beat egg whites and set aside. In a large bowl, combine 2/3 c of cocoa and cornstarch. Whisk 3/4 c. of milk into cocoa mixture until completely smooth.

title: maw maw's tea cakes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cream well.
Add flour and baking powder gradually.
Mix well and chill at least 30 minutes.
Roll on floured surface and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fiesta pasta
directions: Prepare pasta according to package and set aside.
In 12-inch skillet, heat oil over medium
heat and saute zucchini, onion, jalapeno peppers and garlic 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, oregano, olives and salt and heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens.
To serve, toss cooked pasta with vegetable mixture. Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes four side-dish servings.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies; mix with melted butter.
Reserve 1 cup for top. Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ice cream, sauce, Cool Whip and then crumbs on top.
Freeze 24 hours.

title: pecan roll
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft-ball stage.
Add dates and stir until dissolved.
Add pecans.
Stir until firm.
Pour on buttered freezer paper and make into roll.
Refrigerate.

title: apple crisp coffee cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla until well mixed.
Peel and core apple, then chop.
Stir 1/2 of the flour mixture into the sugar mixture.
Stir in sour cream.
Then stir in sour cream and remaining flour mixture and apple.
Spread in pan.
Crush nuts and mix together brown sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over coffee cake.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: microwave vegetable casserole
directions: Combine corn, green beans and cream of potato soup in 2-quart microwave dish.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Cover with onions and cheese.
Microwave for 2 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: biscuit pizza crust
directions: Soften	yeast
in water.
Add biscuit mix.
Beat vigorously for
minutes.
Dust surface with biscuit mix or flour and knead dough
until smooth.
Divide dough in half and roll in
circle. Place dough circle on baking sheet.
Crimp edges. Brush
dough with
oil.	Fill
with desired toppers.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until dough is done.
Makes 2 (12-inch) pizza crusts.

title: stuffed mushrooms appetizer
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Cut out stems and dice finely.
Crush Ritz crackers to make crumbs.
In a medium frying pan, saute onions and diced stems in 2 tablespoons of butter until cooked. Add butter and cook until butter is melted.
Pour over cracker crumbs and toss.
Add Parmesan cheese and 1/3 cup Zesty Italian dressing and mix until a soft stuffing.
Add more Italian dressing if needed.
Stuff each mushroom cap with filling and place on baking sheet.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: holly farm potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and quarter.
Leave the peelings on.
Roll potatoes in mixture of flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in a pan with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn them each over and bake 20 minutes longer or until done.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Cut boneless chicken into pieces and pound thin.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Dust with flour.
Brown pieces of chicken in olive oil, drain on aper towels.
add butter/margarine to pan. Add a sprinkle of parsley.
Add Marsala wine.
Place chicken back in pan and coat with mixture.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Server with angel hair pasta or rice.

title: strawberry short cake(serves 4)
directions: Wash strawberries before using.
Do not soak in water.
Remove stems and hulls.
Drain thoroughly.
Slice strawberries and sprinkle with sugar.
Divide strawberries among 4 cake shells. Prepare whipped cream and spoon over berries.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Tear angel food cake to bits and place in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Blend pudding and milk, then add ice cream.
Beat for 2 minutes on low speed.
Pour over cake and refrigerate.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add frozen strawberries and refrigerate until partially hardened.
Pour over cream filling.

title: cheese olive balls
directions: Grate cheese on coarse end of grater.
Let grated cheese soften at room temperature until consistency of butter.
Add flour and seasoning, working into a dough.
Press mixture around olives and bake on greased baking sheet for 10 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot.

title: special cookies
directions: Combine syrup and sugar in saucepan. Cook over medium heat. Keep stirring until sugar is dissolved and is bubbly. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and then cereal. Stir until all coated. Drop onto wax paper.

title: barbecued rabbit
directions: Rub rabbit with salt and pepper.
Brown in skillet.
Remove. Place in casserole. Combine all ingredients. Mix and pour over rabbit.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste often. Serves 4.

title: welsh currant cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening with a pastry cutter until crumbly.
Add currants.
Beat eggs and add milk until blended; add to dry mixture.
Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours (dough will be stiff).

title: fig pickles
directions: Peel figs (if unpeeled are preferred, pour boiling water over figs and let stand until cool; drain).
Add 3 cups sugar to water and cook until sugar dissolves.
Add figs and cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Add 2 cups sugar and vinegar.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Add to figs; cook gently until figs are clear. Cover and let stand, 12 to 24 hours in a cool place.
Remove spice bag.
Heat to simmering.
Pack hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch space at top.
Adjust caps.
Process pints and quarts 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir gently.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture. Mix until smooth; stir in butter.
Pour into pastry shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: virtuous cheesecake
directions: Blend first four ingredients with electric mixer at medium speed.
Blend in sour cream and egg whites.
Spray 9-inch pie pan with nonfat cooking spray; sprinkle with crumbs.
Pour in cheese mixture and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate for 3 hours.
Top with berries.
Serves 8.

title: raspberry cheese ball
directions: You will also need 2 (1 gallon size) resealable food bags.

title: party salad
directions: Add enough boiling water to pineapple juice to make 2 cups and dissolve jello in it. Mix salt, pimento and cream cheese together and add to hot jello gradually. May soften cheese in microwave. Chill. When it begins to thicken, fold in drained pineapple, celery, 1 cup chopped nuts and whipped topping. Pour into mold or salad bowl and chill to set.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Melt oleo.
Blend in sugar and stir in flour.
Press in pie plate.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Do not overcook.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit tacos
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups cold milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir whipped topping into pudding, very gently, until mixture is all one color. Spoon equal amount pudding into each taco shell.
Top with fruit and then sprinkle coconut on top.
Last, pour a little chocolate syrup over filling.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Blend all ingredients, except coconut, in blender.
Fold in coconut and pour into well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Tastes like custard pie.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook at 450° for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 350°.

title: layered salad
directions: Use a large clear bowl (3-quart).
Layer lettuce; add salad dressing to shells and put next.
Layer cucumbers, tomatoes, tuna or chicken, peas and cheese last.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.
Makes 8 servings or a great salad for a party or shower.

title: barbecue ham sandwiches
directions: Saute onion until tender in butter in saucepan.
(Onion should look transparent.)
Add remaining ingredients; simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Add 2 pounds chopped, chipped ham and heat through. Serve over hamburger rolls.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line a cookie sheet (with sides) with crackers.
Sprinkle the crackers with pecans.
In a pan, boil 2 sticks of margarine and 1/2 cup of sugar for a couple of minutes.
Spoon this mixture over the crackers and bake them for 8 to 10 minutes (300°).
Take the crackers out of the pan and put them on foil to cool.
Store in a tin and refrigerate.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Add rice and salt to boiling water.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 40 minutes. Cook sausage until done and drain off fat.
Add mushroom soup and Worcestershire sauce to rice, sausage, chicken and mushrooms in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs that have been browned in butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk. Beat until smooth.
Gradually beat in powdered sugar, then blend in melted chocolate.
Stir in vanilla, salt and nuts. Press into lightly buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 1 pound.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Stir together until smooth the cornmeal, salt and 1 cup cold water.
In a heavy saucepan bring to boil 4 cups of water.
Add the soaked corn meal, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes. Cover and reduce heat to low and cook about 20 to 30 minutes. Hominy grits can be used instead of cornmeal.

title: aunt mary's slaw
directions: Shred cabbage into a large bowl.
Slice onions and bell pepper very thin.
Put on top of shredded cabbage.
Sprinkle with sugar. In saucepan, heat to boiling the remaining ingredients.
Cool and pour over cabbage.
Do not stir.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Mix before serving.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Fold in cream. Add dry ingredients.
Chill to very cold (dough is soft).
Roll out thick, using powdered sugar on board.
Place on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned.

title: minnie's sweet dill pickles
directions: Soak dill pickles in cold water for 2 hours.
Drain and wipe cucumbers dry.
Slice in 1/4-inches in original jar.
Mix celery seed, clove of garlic and sugar and pour over cucumbers in jar. Fill jar with white vinegar.
Add pickling spices and shake jar until mixture is well mixed.
Place in refrigerator up to one week. Better after 2 weeks.
May add crushed red pepper if you like it a little hot.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt, then set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat together sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla until lightly fluffy.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to beaten mixture.
Beat just until blended after each addition.
Fold in pecans and cherries.
Turn batter into a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: butterscotch pudding walnut cake
directions: Combine.
Mix eggs and pudding mix well.
Beat 2 minutes. Spread in a greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients gently and refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serve on chilled, lettuce-lined plates or bowl.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of a greased casserole dish, then add browned beef and other ingredients in order given. Bake until potatoes are done, about 1 hour and 15 minutes. Bake at 325° to 350°.

title: krispy crunchy cookies
directions: Sift flour once, measure and add baking powder, baking soda and salt; sift again. Cream the shortening.
Add sugars gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well. Add flour, coconut, cereal and vanilla. Blend well. Shape into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: asparagus and egg casserole
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, melt butter and add flour, salt and pepper to gradually make a paste. Add the hot milk slowly, stirring constantly and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and fold in cheese. Place alternate layers of asparagus, sauce and sliced eggs in casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 6.

title: mrs. hoover's tarts
directions: Mix sugar and shortening well, then add other ingredients. Fill unbaked tart shells.
Bake in medium oven for 20 minutes. Yields one dozen.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Mix yeast with sugar, eggs and warm water.
Add oil, salt and flour.
Refrigerate overnight.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll each one out.
Cut into 8 sections.
Let rise 6 hours.
On greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with lemon juice.
Add shrimp and green onions to cream cheese mixture.
Add enough mayonnaise to give a consistency for dipping. Season with Tabasco, salt and pepper. This is much better if made 8 hours ahead.
Add more seasoning if necessary.
Serve with Chicken in a Biscuit crackers.
This will serve 15 people generously.

title: lucky to have any left
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on cooled first layer.
Combine milk and pudding mix; spread on second layer.
Place pecan halves on top.
Chill overnight.

title: jellied pig's feet
directions: Burn skin of pigs feet by holding over gas flame.
This is optional.
Wash well in warm water, then place in kettle and add enough water to cover well.
Bring to a boil and skim.
Lower heat and simmer slowly.
Add garlic, salt, whole black pepper and onion, which has been sliced.
Cook altogether until bones fall apart from the meat
(about 5 or 6 hours).
Strain and pour into dishes; add meat, cut into pieces and let stand overnight in a cool place.
Before serving, sprinkle with paprika.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Run hot water over broccoli until thawed. Drain broccoli. Saute onion until transparent. Combine broccoli, onion, beaten eggs, cottage cheese, corn bread mix and Cheddar cheese. Pour into a lightly greased 8 x 10-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Cut into squares when cooled and serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Beans may be added if desired.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water (just enough to do the job). Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Combine all ingredients together to make dough.
Make up like biscuits.
Bake immediately at 375° until golden brown.

title: cheese snappy wafers
directions: Cut softened butter into flour.
Mix in softened cheese, cayenne and salt.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls and flatten with a glass bottom.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 15 minutes!

title: chicken or pork fried rice
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Beat eggs and add to skillet until set.
Put aside.
Add rest of oil; cook onion, green pepper and garlic 5 minutes or until tender; stir in meat.
Add soy sauce and rice.
Cover and reduce heat for 5 minutes.
Add eggs; stir and serve.

title: california salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in a bowl, starting with the lettuce on the bottom.
Cover. Refrigerate overnight. Mix well just before serving.

title: apple pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Mix flour, soda and cinnamon.
Gradually add to sugar, butter and eggs.
Add apples.
Do not mix any longer than necessary.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Whip at high speed until of spreading consistency.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Arrange 2 bananas on bottom of prepared pastry shell.
Pour filling over bananas.
Cover.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Spread top with whipped cream; garnish with additional banana slices.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: ground deer jerky
directions: Preparation time:
16 to 20 hours.
Mix meat and ingredients then place in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Then roll in thin strips on cookie sheet.
Bake at 150° for 4 to 8 hours or when dry.
When dry, store in airtight container in refrigerator or freezer.

title: big appetite pancakes(makes 85 servings)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk.
Add dry ingredients and oil.
Mix well. Spoon batter on hot griddle.
Brown on both sides.

title: dip in bread bowl
directions: Combine last 7 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, cut top off bread and hollow bread by pulling out small chunks of bread.
Cut the top of the bread into pieces.
Spoon mixture into hollowed out bread.
Arrange bread pieces around bread bowl on a large plate or platter.
Dip bread into dip.
Eat bread bowl when dip is gone.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Liquify all ingredients in a blender.
Add more milk if needed for desired thickness.
Makes 1 large glass.
Drink right away.

title: chewy cocoa brownies
directions: Stir together sugar, butter and water in bowl. Stir in eggs; stir in vanilla. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; stir into sugar mixture. Stir in nuts. Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out slightly sticky. Cool in pan.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In hot butter in Dutch oven or deep kettle, saute onions, with salt, until golden.
Stir in well 1 1/2 teaspoons paprika and meat.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add 4 1/2 teaspoons paprika and enough water to just cover meat.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until meat is fork-tender, adding more water toward end of cooking time if you want extra gravy.
Serve with boiled noodles, poppy or caraway noodles, mashed potatoes or hot fluffy rice. Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: sausage-mushroom breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: peach pie
directions: Place peaches in oblong pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over peaches. Pack down with hand.
Melt butter or margarine and pour over cake mix and peaches.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes until right thickness.
If you want to use Mozzarella cheese, stir it in just before serving.

title: hazelnut lebkuchen
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold in sifted dry ingredients carefully, then spread over Back-Oblaten (wafer papers, available at a German delicatessen). Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil or bake chicken; pull off bones.
Mix first 4 ingredients together for sauce.
Place chicken in tortillas and 2 tablespoons of sauce.
Add a little bit of cheese.
Roll up and place in pan. Pour rest of sauce over enchiladas and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix yeast with water and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients, then add yeast.
Knead for 12 minutes.
Let rise in bowl until doubled.
Make into rolls and put in pans.
Let rise again until doubled.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes. When done, brush tops with butter.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Place 1 layer of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Spread in layers over cake:
1/2 pie filling, 1/2 pineapple, 1 cup coconut, 1 box prepared pudding, 2 1/2 cups whipped topping and 1/2 cup nuts.
Add second layer of cake and layer other ingredients as before.
Garnish with cherries.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients with lemon yogurt.
Serve with cheese and crackers.
(No salt, sugar and only a trace of fat in the nuts.)

title: candied yams
directions: Empty yams in dish. Sprinkle with rest of ingredients. Butter to cover in patties. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: decorator icing
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients
with mixer until very creamy. Very slowly add cold water, beating all the time.
Then add the powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
It should be very thick. Keep covered while not in use.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all.
Chill, then roll into a ball.

title: chili con carne
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, over high heat, cook beef, onion and garlic, stirring often, until all pan juices evaporate.
Stir in chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, kidney beans and tomato sauce.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring often.
Skim fat from chili, if any.
Serves 8 and freezes well.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Seedless grapes or mandarin oranges may be added.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter; add flour and blend.
Add beet liquid and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and cloves.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Add drained beets; heat thoroughly.

title: microwave vegetarian black-bean enchiladas
directions: Drain and rinse beans, chop tomatoes with juice.
Combine onions and garlic in microproof dish, cover.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir in seasonings.
Cover and microwave 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes and juice.
Microwave, uncovered, 3 minutes.
Transfer 1 cup tomato mixture to bowl and add beans and toss to combine. Reserve remaining mixture for topping.
For each enchilada, sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese down center of tortilla.
Top with 1 heaping tablespoon green chilies and 1/2 cup bean mixture.
Roll up and place seam side down in a 13 x 9-inch microwaveproof casserole. Repeat with remaining tortillas and ingredients.
Spoon remaining tomato mixture over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Cover and microwave 4 minutes, turning dish 1/2 way at 2 minutes if microwave does not have a rotating disc.
Sprinkle with green onions and serve.

title: indiana crumb cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, melted butter and flour in bowl. Remove 1 cup of mixture. Add rest of ingredients. Pour into buttered pan. Sprinkle the 1 cup mixture on top. Bake 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: saucy cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, egg and salt.
Shape into 50 meat balls. Place in a shallow baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Broil until brown; turn once.
Spoon off fat.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off wings and put in baking dish. Blend ingredients and pour over chicken. Turn to coat chicken.
Cook on high in microwave for 30 min.
Cook another 20 min.
or until tender and sauce is thick, let stand for 5 min.
uncovered

title: german baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Combine all ingredients in large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Also good in crock-pot.

title: paczki
directions: Beat eggs with sugar; add cool melted butter and beat well. Add rind, salt and warm cream.
Beat well.
Add flour slowly and continue to beat.
Add yeast, dissolved in warm milk and mix thoroughly.
Beat dough about 10 minutes and set in bowl to rise. When doubled, punch down and let rise again.
Proceed to fill and fry.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Boil vegetables and potatoes together until done.
Stir in tomatoes and hamburger.
Add other ingredients and boil about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring to boil water and butter until butter melts.
All at once, add flour and salt.
Stir until dough comes away from sides of pan.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Spread in 1 inch deep cookie sheet type pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Pierce with fork all over.
Let cool before putting topping on.
For topping, make pudding according to package directions, then beat in cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Top with cool whip.
Put on topping of choice if desired (chocolate or caramel syrup, etc.).

title: clams
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Add clams; simmer 5 minutes.
Put on pasta.

title: best carrot cake
directions: Mix everything together in a large bowl, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Divide the batter between three 8 or 9-inch cake pans, greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 325° for approximately 40 minutes.
For smaller cake pans, bake a few minutes longer.

title: princess' sad cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.

title: macaroni and cheese with fish sticks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Cook and stir margarine, onion, salt and pepper over medium heat until onion is slightly tender.
Blend in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Place macaroni in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir cheese sauce into macaroni.
Arrange fish sticks on macaroni.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini-corn pudding
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in butter and oil until tender. Add zucchini and cook slowly 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in corn and seasonings.
Cool.
Add beaten egg yolks, cheese, melted butter and sugar.
Beat egg whites until stiff, fold into vegetable mixture. Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Set in pan of hot water. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
May be baked ahead and reheated.
An excellent compliment to a baked ham or turkey!

title: spanish onions(encasserole with almonds)
directions: Parboil onions in small amount of water.
Drain well.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add chicken broth and cream, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Combine sauce, onions and almonds.
Add seasonings and pour into buttered casserole. Bake in water bath in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle cheese, mixed with bread crumbs over top and brown under broiler.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Break 1/2 the cake up in bottom of a fairly small punch bowl.
Make the pudding mix with 5 cups milk.
Pour 1/2 the pudding mix over the cake, then add 1 can of cherry pie filling, 1/2 can crushed, drained pineapple and 2 1/2 sliced bananas.
Mix the whipped topping and the nuts; put 1/2 of this over mixture. Repeat all the layers, ending with nut topping mixture and decorate with cherries.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
This recipe may be cut in half to serve a smaller group.

title: free-form peanut butter cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together shortening, peanut butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.

Stir together flour, soda and salt; stir into peanut butter mixture. Form dough into balls and ropes; put on ungreased cookie sheets. Push dough together and flatten with hands to make animals, people or other shapes.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheets 1 minute; remove to wire racks.
Makes 3 dozen large cookies.
This is a good recipe to make with your child.

title: cocktail meatballs (300)
directions: Mix meats and spices together. Add salt, pepper and parsley flakes. Shape into tiny meatballs and bake for 20 minutes at 350°, shaking occasionally. Remove balls and put drippings in pan on low heat. Add V-8 juice, broths and bouillon cubes. Heat until juice is reduced slightly. Serve with sauce in chafing dish.

title: monterey rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then cover with grated sharp Cheddar cheese and put under broiler.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Break frozen broccoli apart and place in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour mushroom soup diluted with milk over broccoli.
Add onion.
Add Pepperidge Farm dressing prepared for crumbly stage on top of broccoli mixture and stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, lemon pepper and pepper.
Work up together and pack mixture into a Pyrex loaf dish (microwaveable). Microwave on High for 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Fill buns and wrap each in foil until ready to use.
Bake in 300° oven for about 20 minutes or until filling is hot and cheese melted.

title: hot coffee sundae
directions: Melt butter with sugars in a small pot.
Remove from flame. Add vanilla, coffee and milk.
Over low heat, cook and stir until smooth and thickened (about 1 1/2 minutes).
Pour over ice cream. Makes one large serving.

title: chocolate "hideaway" mousse
directions: Combine brownie mix, hot water, oil and egg in large bowl. Beat 50 strokes by hand.
Spread in a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan which has been greased and floured (line with wax paper; also grease and flour).
Spread mix even in pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool on rack 5 minutes.
Turn pan upside-down over cake rack and unmold.
Gently pull off wax paper; cool.

title: hawaiian harvard beets
directions: Heat beets in their own juice.
Add drained pineapple chunks and heat until simmering.
Retain liquid.
Stir pineapple liquid, lemon juice and cornstarch together.
Stir into simmering beets. Stir and cook until thickened.
Serves 6.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add cheese and tomatoes.
Keep warm in a warmer or crock-pot.
Serve with nachos or potato chips.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in sugar.
Add water, flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend in pumpkin and oil.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour into 2 loaf pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: gran's custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until smooth and foamy.
Heat milk to scalding.
Do not boil.
Pour sugar and egg mixture slowly into milk.
Stir continually and cook until the custard coats a metal spoon.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Gradually stir sugar into cream cheese.
Add salt and vanilla. Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Cool slightly and stir into cheese mixture.
Add nuts.
For softer fudge, add cream. Press into well-greased shallow pan or roll into log.
Chill until firm.
Cut when set.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: h. hiser taffy
directions: Add ingredients in order of listing.
Stir slightly.
Boil to 249°.
Turn burner off.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Shake kettle slightly until soda foams.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken at 350° for 40 minutes.
Break chicken into pieces and place in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Mix sour cream and chicken broth and pour over chicken, then put cracker meal and another can of chicken broth.
Slice butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Put together in following order:

Crumble one layer of cooled cake in bottom of large bowl; mix pudding as directed and pour over crumbled cake; crumble 2nd layer of cake over pudding mix; layer drained pineapple over second cake layer; layer cherry pie filling over pineapple; sprinkle coconut over cherry pie filling; spread with whipped topping.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Quarter chicken.
Combine beaten eggs with milk or with buttermilk.
Dip chicken into milk mixture; flour thoroughly and season.
Cook chicken until golden brown.
Do not overcrowd; better to use 2 frying pans or a deep fryer set at 365°.
Cook 13 to 15 minutes in a deep fryer.

title: sunday best beans
directions: Drain beans and mushrooms.
Set aside.
Fry bacon crisp.
Set aside.
Pour out grease.
Saute onion and mushrooms.
Add to bacon (crumbled), and green beans.
Mix well and turn to low and cover. Heat 15 minutes.
Slice Velveeta and place strips on top and cover until melted.
Then stir into beans.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Wash and pick beans.
Cover beans with water and bring to a boil.
Turn off stove and let beans soak for 1 hour.
Saute green pepper, onion and garlic in olive oil.
Drain beans.
Add to pepper and onion mixture.
Add oregano, bay leaf and salt.
Add water to cover beans and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add vinegar 5 to 10 minutes before beans are done.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: casserole date cookies
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy. Stir remaining ingredients in; turn into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir well with wooden spoon while hot.
Cool; form into small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.

title: polynesian bake
directions: Combine rice and margarine.
Toss lightly.
Add ham, pineapple, green pepper and barbecue sauce; mix well.
Place individual servings of rice mixture on squares of foil.
Bring corners together and twist.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: new waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, gently toss together pineapple, apple, celery, grapes, walnuts and kiwi fruit.
In a small bowl stir together the mayonnaise or salad dressing, yogurt and honey; fold gently into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill for 2 to 4 hours. Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: roast turkey, pheasant, chicken or duck
directions: Fold foil in
shape of boat to fit bird.
Place bird in foil boat.
Mix ingredients; pour over bird and close the foil tight over
bird.
Sprinkle
lightly
with parsley flakes and paprika before folding foil.
Cook on back yard cooker on low heat until tender, about 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in soup, milk, cheese and seasonings.
Heat until cheese melts.
Combine with tuna, macaroni and peas.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Crumble potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 to 45 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl (except cornflakes).
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle topping with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: In a large bowl beat butter with with mixer on medium high for 30 seconds.
Add half the flour and all the sugar milk and vanilla. Beat until combined, beat in remaining flour.
Stir in cherries and pecans.
Shape dough into two 8 inch rolls, roll each in coconut. Wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap, chill 4 to 48 hours.
Cut dough into 1/4 inch slices and place on ungreased sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 - 12 minutes.

title: apple muffins
directions: Combine in a bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Blend the shortening, egg, milk and apple.
Add to the dry ingredients and stir just until ingredients are blended.
Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full.
Top with brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Thinly slice cucumber (you may peel or leave peel on).
Mix all other ingredients and pour over cucumber.
Refrigerate 6 hours.

title: corn soup with crabmeat
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cook over medium heat.
Add corn and broth.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add crabmeat and continue cooking 5 more minutes.
Stir in the half and half cream and enjoy!

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: If you use the pumpkin pie mix omit spices.

title: apple salad
directions: In a sauce pan combine pineapple an sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes. Add jell-o.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; stir until mixture is thoroughly combined.
Cool.
Fold in apples, nuts, celery and whipped topping.
Pour into a 9 inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: pizza roll
directions: Roll out bread dough, use flour underneath.
Brush with butter/oregano mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and meat. Add mushrooms.
Roll up the long way and pinch dough together. Lay the dough on cookie sheet, pinched side down.
Brush with butter/oregano mixture again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until it bursts open and cheese oozes out.
Cut into slices and dip in pizza sauce.

title: hot rolls
directions: Let rise 45 minutes. Then melt margarine and squeeze out roll in margarine in little balls. Put in pan, then let rise again 45 minutes. If warm, you don't have to let them rise that long.

title: peanutty gems
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and peanut butter together until smooth.
Add 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
At slow speed, gradually beat in flour mixture until well combined.

title: smothered potatoes(microwave)
directions: In a deep casserole dish, slice potatoes (thinly) and spread in a layer in bottom of dish.
Add salt and pepper; sprinkle with onion and put about 3 teaspoons of margarine.
Repeat in layers until all potatoes have been sliced and seasoned; cover. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir and cook for another 5 to 8 minutes.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: daddy's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cream shortening with sugar, vanilla and cinnamon. Continue creaming until light and fluffy. Beat eggs and blend in. Add melted chocolate when cooled. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating until smooth. Pour batter into 2 well-greased 8-inch cake pans. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Press hamburger into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion soup.
Spread on cream of mushroom soup.
Line frozen Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Leftover portions are delicious reheated.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cream, syrup and vinegar; bring to a boil. Boil until soft ball stage. Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Pour in a buttered square Pyrex dish.
Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: anti-cellulite bar
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Combine all ingredients, except seed. Mix for 5 minutes.
Put into 10 x 10-inch pan and press top with seed.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes; let cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 15 bars.

title: maple flavored syrup
directions: Cook brown sugar, salt and water in large saucepan for 3 to 4 minutes (or until thick).
Add flavorings; makes 1 1/4 cups.
No need to butter waffles.

title: egg salad
directions: Use on party bread - open face or as a sandwich.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread, onion, milk, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape mixture in one-inch balls.
Melt shortening in a skillet and brown the meatballs.
Pour off the fat.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly until melted.
Add meatballs, stir gently but thoroughly.
Simmer for 30 minutes in an open cooker.

title: bagged turkey
directions: You will also need 1 Reynolds turkey bag.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Roll cubed meat in flour and fry in hot butter until browned. Add garlic powder and onion and saute until onion becomes transparent.
Add water and cook until meat becomes tender (about 30 minutes).
Add soup and mushrooms and continue cooking, uncovered, over low heat until mixture becomes thick (about 20 minutes).
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: impossible chicken pie
directions: Cook and bone chicken; cut into small pieces and place in a baking dish.
Melt oleo and pour over chicken.
Sift together salt, pepper, baking powder and flour; mix with milk.
Pour over chicken.
Heat soup and broth to boiling; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
It makes its own crust.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Make
bite size meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes. Set aside.
Combine sauce ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Drain
meatballs.
Put in baking dish.
Pour sauce over
the meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put in chafing
dish or crock-pot just a few minutes before serving.
Add the pineapple and green pepper.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of 12-cup fluted cake pan (or bundt pan).
Sprinkle wheat germ in pan, and roll and tap pan to coat (similar to flouring a greased pan). Shake out excess wheat germ.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir in oatmeal.
Set aside.
Mix slightly beaten egg whites, brown sugar, cooking oil, milk, vanilla and raisins.
Mix thoroughly. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop batter by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack.

title: cheese spread
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature.
Blend thoroughly and chill.

title: prego meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix another cup of Prego with 1/2 cup water.
Pour over top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for one hour, uncovered.

title: aunt lucille's sweet potato souffle crunch
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Pour Topping over sweet potato mixture.
Spread evenly. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple. Add drained fruit cocktail.
Add Cool Whip,
marshmallows and nuts. Chill.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 9x9-inch or 13x9-inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs, then layer coconut.
Layer chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Sprinkle nuts over chips.
Pour condesed milk evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 min.
Do Not Overbake.

title: sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Cut larger tomatoes in quarters, cherry tomatoes in half. Arrange on cookie sheet, cut side up.
Season to taste with salt. Place cookie sheet in a 200° oven for about 7 hours.

Watch that tomatoes do not burn. When done, tomatoes should have a dried, shriveled appearance. Dip each tomato in vinegar and layer in sterile glass jars. Cover tomatoes with olive oil. Add herbs. Tomatoes will last for months in or out of the refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole with biscuits(kentucky bluegrass recipe)
directions: Cook celery, onion and green pepper in butter until soft. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add the chicken broth and cook until mixture thickens.
Stir constantly.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown meat in a skillet and drain.

title: spiced pear salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: In a medium bowl, mix brown sugar, sherry, reserved juice, vinegar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Microwave at High 1 to 3 minutes or until boiling, stirring after half the time.
Add pear halves, stirring to coat.
Microwave at High 1 to 3 minutes or until heated.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: strawberry-lemonade pie
directions: Sweeten strawberries overnight with 1 cup sugar.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into pie shells and chill thoroughly.

title: meringue sticks
directions: Combine sugars.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar mixture a tablespoon at a time while beating.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Beat in vanilla.
Put meringue in pastry tube or bag.
Using a star tip, pipe meringue onto parchment paper on cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven door.
Turn off oven.
Allow to cool in oven 2 hours.
Remove and serve.

title: date balls
directions: Cook in saucepan until it boils the butter, sugar, dates and egg.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Let cool until you can make small balls.
Roll balls in confectioners sugar. Place on wax paper to cool.

title: quick pudding cookies
directions: Cream the shortening; add sugar and pudding.
Add eggs; mix. Add flour mixture.
Drop onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: best-ever veal and peppers
directions: Cut peppers into 1-inch squares.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet over high heat.
When oil ripples, add peppers and cook until crisp-tender.
Remove with slotted spoon and set aside.

title: canned imitation crushed pineapple
directions: Peel zucchini; grind and measure.
Combine all ingredients in large pot and cook 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and place in clean canning jars.
Seal and cold pack for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt Crisco.
Stir in cookie crumbs. Press firmly on bottom of an ungreased 9-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
Place cream cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk gradually, beating until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat just until combined.
Toss 1/2 cup chocolate chips with flour to coat.
Stir chips into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips over
top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes.
Loosen sides of pan; cool for 30 minutes. Remove sides and refrigerate.

title: hot buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in bowl, tossing wings in mixture and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes or until fully cooked.

title: quick russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and put into a tightly closed container. Use 2 to 3 heaping teaspoons of mixture for each cup hot water. Will keep up to six months.

title: banana bread
directions: Alternate flour and soda water; bake in 350° oven 1 hour or until done.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Blend cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and diced onions into a mixture.
Allow to stay at room temperature.
Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine 2 cups graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Stir in cereal.
Place cereal in large brown paper bag, then shake.

title: methodist punch
directions: Boil sugar and 2 cups water.
Cool. Add remaining ingredients and 1 quart water.
Chill and pour over ice in punch bowl.
Add ice cream last just before serving.
Yields 25 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: snack sauce
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a quart jar.
Seal tightly and shake until well blended.
Add pineapple.
Cover and blend together.
Chill.
Serve over leftover cake, gingerbread, etc.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Rolls should be touching sides of each other.
This will be the crust. Bake (according to package temperature) for about 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown.
Allow to cool.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and party dip together.
Spread on top of the crust.
Layer chopped vegetables on top of the dip mix, then top with grated cheese.

title: ensaymada
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter.
Add flour.
Knead until smooth.
Cover and let rise until double.
Shape like (cinnamon rolls) and let rise again.
Bake at 375° until slightly brown.
Before serving, spread butter on top of the rolls and sprinkle with sugar.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Mix cake by box instructions.
Pour half of mix in 9x13 in. pan.
Melt caramels in butter and add milk.
Spread over cake. Add rest of cake mix and bake for 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: bologna spread
directions: Mix together.
Makes a good sandwich spread.

title: maid rites(ham or hamburger?)
directions: Cook hamburger in double boiler. This steam cooks it--not fry. Cook for at least 2 hours on top of stove. I put mine in a crock pot on high until it starts to cook, then on low for 6 to 8 hours. Stir off and on.

title: easy graham bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and milk.
Add margarine; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in well-greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit, 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon flour in pan; dot with butter.
Take egg, sugar and shortening; mix.
Add 1/2 cup milk, alternating with flour, baking powder and salt; blend well.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until done.

title: hearty baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute vegetables lightly.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Combine all ingredients in large covered pot or Dutch oven.
Bake for 40 to 60 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend ingredients.
Beat smooth.
Pour over 3 cups rhubarb in 9 or 10-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Top with lattice crust.
Bake in a hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes, then in moderate oven (350°) for about 30 minutes.

title: mexican rice
directions: Fry rice in hot oil with onion and garlic until lightly browned.
Drain off oil.
Add boiling broth, parsley, chile and salt.
Cover tightly and simmer for 25 minutes without lifting the lid.
Serve with any main dish.
Serves 4.

title: 24-hour layer salad
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish with bite-size pieces of crisp lettuce.
Sprinkle with chopped green pepper and red pepper. Add layer of chopped celery, chopped onion and uncooked frozen peas.
Combine the sugar and mayonnaise.
Spread over these ingredients.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ms. prunella cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs.
Add prunes, dry ingredients, pecans and milk.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: mild chicken curry
directions: In large pot, combine chicken, 1/2 of curry, salt, pepper and garlic; add water.
Boil completely.
Remove bones and skin, but keep broth.
Put chicken back in 1/2 of natural broth and add canned broth and chopped tomatoes and add rest of curry and more if desired.
Simmer until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine mustard, ketchup, brown sugar and bacon.
Put one can of beans in a baking dish.
Pour 1/2 of sugar mixture on top.
Add second can of beans and pour rest of sugar mixture over it.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: coconut custard
directions: Combine all ingredients
in a blender; mix on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour
into
ungreased
9	x
11-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with grated coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix horseradish and catsup to taste.
Spread on top of softened cheese.
Top with crabmeat.
Serve with crackers.

title: brunch egg bake
directions: Toss 1/2 of cheese and sprinkle in the bottom of a slightly oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute in pan, mushrooms, onions, pepper and margarine until tender, then arrange over cheese, then sprinkle on ham and the remaining cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream
together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of cocoa and
part of food coloring.
Add this mix and rest of food coloring
to
shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately to cream mixture, starting with vinegar.
Add baking soda, then vanilla in batter; mix well.
Bake
in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350°.
Test for doneness; do not overbake.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugars.
Beat until light. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add to first mixture.
Work in the peanuts, corn flakes and oatmeal.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip balls in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In a large bowl, stir together egg whites, bananas, sugar and oil.
Stir flour mixture into banana mixture just until moistened.
Spray an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack before taking loaf out of pan.

title: blissful isle punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Makes 2 gallons.

title: polish sausage supper
directions: Put sausage in the bottom of a large kettle.
Cut cabbage into 6 wedges.
Core and place on top of sausage.
Peel potatoes.
Cut in half lengthwise and place on top of cabbage.
Husk and remove silk from corn.
Place corn on top of potatoes.
Pour broth over layered meat and vegetables.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 45 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Put all ingredients into slow cooker or crock-pot. Cook overnight. Put in refrigerator to cool. Once cool, remove fat, slice thin and put back into broth. Serve over fresh Italian rolls.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken in egg, then bread crumbs. In 9 x 13 inch baking dish, arrange chicken.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes.
Pour pasta sauce over chicken, top with cheese.
Bake an additional 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve with hot cooked pasta.

title: buttery onion soup
directions: In a large kettle, saute onions in butter over low heat until tender and transparent, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Blend in flour. Gradually add broth and milk; cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more; reduce heat to low.
Add cheese and stir constantly until melted.
Do not boil.
Season to taste.
Serve with croutons.

title: parmesan popcorn
directions: In small saucepan melt margarine.
Stir cheese into melted butter; let cool about five minutes.
Place 12 cups popped popcorn in large bowl.
Pour the cheese mixture on top of the popcorn. Toss with forks, coating the popcorn evenly with the cheese mixture.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Thoroughly mix the dry ingredients.
Cut in the lard.
Add enough water to make a stiff dough.
Divide into 12 balls; roll out onto a lightly floured board, making them as thin as possible. Bake for about 2 minutes on each side in an ungreased cast-iron skillet over medium heat.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: frozen chocolate mint squares
directions: In a
small bowl, combine crushed wafers and margarine. Press mixture firmly onto
bottom
of a 9 x 13-inch pan.	In a medium mixing
bowl,
beat the marshmallow cream, mint extract and green food coloring with an electric mixer on medium speed until smooth. Fold
in
cup
of the semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
In a small
mixing bowl, whip cream until soft peaks form; fold	into marshmallow cream mixture.	Spread over crust in pan.
Sprinkle remaining
semi-sweet chocolate pieces over dessert.
Cover and freeze at least 6 hours.
At serving time, remove from freezer and
let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
For easy serving, place warm moist cloth on the bottom of the pan. Cut into squares.
Makes 8 servings.

title: icebox salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail (juice is not used in this recipe).
Mix all remaining ingredients with the pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Chill and serve.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir onion in margarine in 2 quart saucepan until onion is tender.
stir in remaining ingredients except shrimp and rice.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes. Stir in shrimp; heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine 1/2 cup melted butter with all ingredients, except cornflake crumbs.
Mix in a 3-quart casserole. Mix cornflakes with remaining 1/4 cup of butter; sprinkle flakes over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans in hot water for 1 1/2 hours.
Cook beans and bacon together in water to cover beans for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not drain. Add remaining ingredients; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: frosty date muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in oats and dates.
Add oil, egg and milk.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Place one date half in each muffin cup.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Drizzle with powdered sugar frosting.
If desired, a few drops of orange extract can be added to the frosting for extra flavor.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add crushed vanilla wafers with milk.
Add pecans and coconut.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: barbecue beaver
directions: Wash beaver and boil with pickling spices for 30 minutes. Take meat out of water and place in baking pan.
Slice up onion and place over meat.
Salt, pepper and garlic meat.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, stirring occasionally.
Then take barbecue sauce, Lea & Perrins, mix together and pour over meat.
Bake 1 1/2 more hours at 300°.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Cream all ingredients together except melted margarine.
Add margarine last.
Bake in unbaked pie shells at 325° for 30 minutes or until pie tester comes out clean.
Make 2 large pies.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken; bone and dice.
Cook seashells.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, combine 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stir in egg yolks.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Spoon hot filling into pie shell.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream 4 egg yolks, sugar and butter.
Add milk; put soda in first cup of flour and add gradually to mixture.
Gradually add rest of flour (may not need all 3 cups).
Roll batter into rolls and chill.
Then slice to bake.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: sparkling grape juice punch
directions: Mix and cool.
Serve with ice ring or crushed ice.

title: super frito pie
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic (onion may be cooked with meat or served raw on pie).
Drain; add chili powder, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over corn chips and garnish with remaining ingredients.
This is delicious!
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: squash continental
directions: In a large skillet over moderate heat, saute onion in butter. Remove onion and set aside.
Cut 8 small zucchini squash into 1/2-inch rounds.
Saute in skillet with remaining butter.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Cook covered with tight-fitting lid for 6 to 8 minutes;
add onion.
Blend in with a fork.
Do not overcook as squash becomes soggy and loses it shape.

title: laurie's super nachos
directions: Combine salsa ingredients in bowl and set aside.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk, salt and corn.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until firm.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Soak gelatin in
cup juice.
Heat rest of juice to boiling and
dissolve gelatin,.
Stir in salt and other spices and vegetables.
Arrange a layer of sliced olives in bottom of molds. Add a
thin
layer	of
juice.
Cool
a bit, then fill molds. Chill until firm. Serve on greens of your choice.

title: nacho chip chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°. Bake 20 minutes. Boil chicken and cut in bite size pieces. Mix chicken, chicken soup, tomatoes and green chilies (drain can for a mild flavor), taco seasoning and 2 cups of cheese. Put chips in a greased baking dish. Spread mixture over chips. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top. Bake until cheese is melted and started to brown. Can garnish with shredded lettuce and sour cream.

title: sweet pea's chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until crisp-tender.
Combine salad dressing, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until melted.

title: pesto
directions: Cook rigatoni in large pot with 1/4 cup of oil; when done, pour most of water down drain.
Leave enough water in bottom of pan so noodles are moist.
Add 1/4 cup of oil, garlic and large amounts of basil; keep adding basil and stirring until noodles are coated with it.
If desired, stir in some olives.
This can be served hot or cold.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter in a saucepan.
Cook until tender.
Add creamed corn, beaten eggs, salt, sugar, milk and flour.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Set casserole in shallow pan of water.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: quick shrimp dip
directions: Mash or blend all ingredients together; serve with chips.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Pull cake apart in pieces and spread in a large shallow dish. Mix pudding according to package directions and spread over cake pieces.
Mix sliced berries and gel.
Spread over pudding. Spread Cool Whip over strawberries and gel mixture.
Place whole strawberries on Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.

title: peachy barbecued pork chops
directions: Put chops in an oblong pan.
Drain peaches, reserving syrup. In a saucepan, blend 1 cup syrup, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, onion, flour, mustard, cloves, salt and pepper.
Heat to a boil. Pour over chops.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Turn over once.
Arrange peaches around chops.
Bake 5 minutes longer, basting with sauce.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, cream of tartar and salt together.
Add to other ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator.
Mix 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon
in
a bowl.
Take 1 teaspoon of chilled dough.
Roll into balls.
Roll
in
cinnamon
mixture.
Bake
for
to 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet at 450°.

title: meat loaf *
directions: Have beef at room temperature, then mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Grease loaf pan or Pyrex dish well and pour mixture in.
Cook in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until done.
Don't overcook as it will be stiff and dry.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine diced cheese, Ro-Tel, garlic, chili powder and cumin. Heat until melted.	Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine lettuce and chopped tomatoes.
Brown hamburger, onions and green peppers together and cool.	 Once cool, add Fritos to meat.
Toss together with lettuce and tomatoes.	Pour cheese sauce over mixture and toss just before serving.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Drain the clams.
Save the juice.
In a heavy skillet, saute garlic and scallions in olive oil until soft.
Add clam juice and simmer, covered, until juice is reduced to half (10 minutes).
Add clams, parsley, salt and pepper.
Serve within 5 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 2 servings.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix well; batter will be stiff.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: todd house baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place as many pieces of chicken as will fit into a baking dish.
Generously sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt.
Add a little water in bottom of dish; cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Serve immediately.

title: mid's classic chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients but chicken, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Season pieces of chicken with salt and pepper; lay on top.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours or 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fragrance of christmas
directions: Simmer in open pan on stove during Holidays.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Brown steak in hot oil in large skillet.
Combine bouillon, soy sauce, sugar and sherry. Add half to the meat.
Push meat to side of pan.
Add onions and celery; cook on low heat for 3 minutes. Add rest of bouillon mixture, bamboo shoots, mushrooms and spinach.
Cook 3 minutes. Add green onions and cook 1 minute. Put hot, drained pasta on one side of platter, sukiyaki on the other and serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat.
Add nuts, apples and raisins.
Stir thoroughly.
Add soda, cinnamon, salt and vanilla. Stir in flour.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tim's chicken fried rice(kao pael gai)
directions: Slice chicken across grain into 1/8 x 1-inch strips.
Peel yellow onion, slice into thin strips.
Set aside separately. Slice white and green parts of green onions diagonally into 1/8-inch pieces; set aside.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together rest of ingredients except corn flakes and butter.
Pour over potatoes. Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: black forest cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 8 or 9-inch round pans. Cool on cooling rack.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Remove from heat; blend dry cake mix into hot pudding.
Mixture will be quite thick and spongy.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shanghai chicken
directions: Skin and bone chicken; cut into small cubes.
Saute in oil until firm and white.
Stir in celery and cook, about 1 1/2 minutes or until crisp and tender.
Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts, soup, soy sauce and pepper.
Cook 1 minute longer; stir in pimento and onions.
Heat but do not overcook.
Spoon over rice and top with noodles and soy sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
