directions: Mix and store in an airtight container. Use 3 heaping tablespoonfuls per cup of boiling water. Great to give to a friend.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients. Makes about 3 1/2 cups salsa.

title: true beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut into bite size pieces.
Brown meat, onions and mushrooms in butter.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender. Drain well. Add next 5 ingredients.
Melt 3/4 stick of margarine in frying pan. Add stuffing and mix well.
Pack into bottom of 2-quart baking pan. Reserve some stuffing for top.
Pour in squash mixture.
Sprinkle on remaining stuffing.
Dot with rest of margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: philly 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Add 2 eggs; mix well.
Pour batter into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool.
For best results, refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.

title: lemon cabbage
directions: Heat wok or skillet to 325° for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add first 4 ingredients and stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Cover.
Reduce heat and steam 2 to 3 minutes or until tender.
Add lemon rind and remaining ingredients.
Mix and continue heating until cabbage is of tenderness desired.
Serve while hot.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix in large Tupperware bowl.
Cover and keep in refrigerator. Take out amount you wish to cook.
Knead and bake.
Let rise for about 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 425° until brown and light.

title: linguini leonardo
directions: Cut asparagus into 2-inch length and microwave for about 5 minutes or steam.

title: sherry chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Pour chicken soup, sour cream and sherry over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is cooked.
Serve over rice.

title: baked corn and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water.
Rinse in cold water and drain. Add the other ingredients.
Bake in oven in casserole for 45 minutes.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine all the dry ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray. Bake 70 to 75 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Allow to cool out of pan before slicing.

title: owen's favorite gingerbread people
directions: Cream thoroughly shortening, brown sugar, molasses and egg. In separate bowl, sift flour and spices.
Slowly stir it into the sugar and egg mixture.
Make sure all ingredients are combined.

title: brisket
directions: Rub
salt
and tenderizer generously on meat.
Line pan with foil and make long enough to cover top.
Put in meat, fat side up.
Add
Worcestershire
sauce,
liquid
smoke
and red pepper. Cover
with
foil
and refrigerate 24 hours.
Cook at 225°	for
8 hours.
Can make sauce by using 1/2 cup juice and 1/2 cup barbecue sauce.

title: crab salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine lettuce, chopped onion, sliced bell pepper, cucumber and crab meat; toss.
In a separate bowl, cream together sour cream, mayonnaise, dill mix and pepper.
Pour over salad just before serving.

title: microwave dump cake
directions: Use 8-inch round glass dish.
Evenly spoon pie filling in and then sprinkle with cake mix.
Pour butter over mixture.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts; sprinkle on top.
Microwave on High for 9 to 11 minutes.
Rotate 1/4 turn halfway through cooking.
Rest for 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream, ice cream or plain.

title: popcorn gumdrop cake
directions: Combine butter and marshmallows until melted.
Add popcorn, peanuts and gumdrops, stirring until blended.
Press into pan. Chill and remove cake from pan to plate.

title: cheesy tuna onion fondue
directions: Mix dry soup and milk in medium saucepan; heat slowly.
When just scalded, add a small portion of cheese and stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Continue to add cheese gradually, stirring constantly, making sure each addition is melted before adding more cheese. Add tuna and parsley.
Turn into fondue saucepan and partially cover flame so mixture is kept just warm.

title: key lime pie
directions: CRUST:
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In medium bowl combine Graham Cracker Crumbs, Sugar and melted butter.
Stir until mixture is evenly moistened.
Press into a 9-inch Pie Plate bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool on a wire rack.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown meat.
Drain fat.
Add onion, pepper and celery.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste.
This is a leaner version of chili, low-fat and delicious.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and mash cream cheese with dressing.
Roll into a ball. Cover thoroughly in nuts.
Serve with bagel chips, crackers, etc. May be frozen.

title: oriental marinade
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Marinate meat for 2 to 3 hours before cooking.
Can be used on beef, pork, or chicken. Baste with sauce as you grill.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Peel and cut lengthwise in thick slices and lay in water until just before dinner.
Wipe dry; sprinkle with pepper and salt.
Dip in beaten egg and roll in crushed crackers.
Fry with the cover on until light brown.

title: corn bread
directions: *Can use 4 tablespoons buttermilk and 1 cup water instead of milk and lemon juice.

title: pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg in cup and add vinegar and 1/2 cup of water.
You may add more water if needed.
Turn out on floured cloth.
Knead to make smooth dough. This makes four 8-inch pie crusts or three 9-inch pie crusts.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Soak chicken in tomato juice mixture for about 1 hour. Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 11 x 13-inch pan with a nonstick spray.
Sprinkle skin side of chicken with garlic and lay chicken in pan.
Sprinkle top side with garlic and oregano and pour tomato mixture over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn chicken over and sprinkle again with garlic and oregano for another 1/2 hour.
Use the juice to baste chicken during the last 1/2 hour and use as sauce over rice or noodles.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and condensed milk until thick and creamy. Fold in the Cool Whip to the milk mixture. Add pineapple and mix well. Add coconut; mix. Pour into a graham cracker crust. Chopped pecans may be sprinkled over the top. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and continue cooking, stirring only occasionally, to hard ball stage (252°), without stirring.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until well done.
Cut off tops and scoop out inside into bowl.
Beat remaining ingredients with potatoes.
Stir in 1/4 medium onion sauteed in 2 tablespoons butter and 1/4 cup grated cheese.
(Save some to sprinkle on top.)
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: fresh apple-pear cobbler
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan, stirring well.
Add water, stirring well.
Bring to boil over medium heat. Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gently stir in pears, apples and raisins.
Spoon mixture into an 8-inch square baking dish that has been coated with cooking spray. Combine flour, 1 tablespoon sugar and baking powder in a bowl.
Add milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop dumpling mixture over apple and pear mixture by level tablespoon.

title: italiano marinara
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, heat oil and cook onion and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, parsley, sugar, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally to break up tomatoes, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix by hand the eggs, sugar and pineapple (juice too).
Mix soda with the flour, then add to mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until cake turns golden brown.
Be sure to use 20 ounces crushed pineapple.

title: barbecue chicken wings(appetizer)
directions: Season wings with garlic powder and onion powder.
Arrange wings, wing end up, in a microwave dish.
Using 15 to 20 wings, you have the choice of making two layers of wings or placing the other layer in another dish.
Cover wings with wax paper loosely. Microwave 8 to 10 minutes on High for a single layer.
Microwave on High 20 minutes for double layer.
Remove from microwave and brush with sauce; serve.

title: brownie chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour and salt into a bowl.
In a saucepan, place butter, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir into sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
In
a separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add vanilla, soda and buttermilk.
Stir into first mixture.
Pour into greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: chocolate chip meltaways
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Add this to butter mixture.
Add vanilla and chocolate chips.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on a rack.
Makes about 7 or 8 dozen cookies.

title: tasty rice and almond casserole
directions: Place the water in a large pan and bring it to a boil.

Brown the sausage and drain off excess fat. Add the celery, onions and green pepper and simmer for 10-15 minutes. When the water is boiling, pour in the rice and soup and allow it to boil gently for 15 minutes. Combine with the sausage and vegetable mixture in a large casserole dish, add the almonds and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 375°f. 190°c. gas mark 5. Uncover and bake for a further 15 minutes.

title: lazy roast
directions: Set roast out in room temperature for 1 hour before cooking. Preheat oven to 375°.
Rub meat well with salt and sprinkle with pepper.
Place meat, fat side up, in shallow roasting pan. Do not cover; do not add water.
Put roast in oven.
Cook just 1 hour. Turn off heat, but do not open door at any time until ready to serve.
Regardless of the length of time meat has been in the oven, reset temperature to 375° and cook 30 to 40 minutes before serving.
Open oven door and remove roast to serving platter. Meat will be brown on out side, medium-rare inside.

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Mix macaroni, tuna, onion and cheese.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Heat soup and water to boiling, stirring frequently. Pour over macaroni mixture.
Bake, uncovered, until mixture is bubbly, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy cream of potato soup or broccoli
directions: In a food processor, puree 1 onion and 3 to 4 carrots.
Put in pot.
Fill pot 2/3 full with remaining cut up carrots and potatoes. Add water until pot is 3/4 full.
Boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
After vegetables are cooked, add water to 3/4 full again. Add creamer and 16 ounces of cheese.
Continue stirring until cheese is melted.
Keep temperature hot.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Bring soup to a low boil and stir in cornstarch mixture. Stir.
(Add more cornstarch mixture if needed to make into a cream soup consistency.)
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Turn temperature to low.
Serve with shredded cheese.

title: turkey cracker stuffing
directions: Crush soda crackers into pieces (do not crush into fine crumbs). Heat milk, margarine and spices in pan. Add cracker crumbs. Add egg and enough chicken broth to moisten. Add to turkey cavity and bake as usual. Makes enough for a 20 pound turkey.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and banana pulp. Blend well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla extract to mixture.
Mix well and stir in nuts.
I do all the mixing by hand with wire whisk.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool well and store overnight before cutting.
Good with 6 to 8 ounces of cream cheese and apricot preserves for tea sandwiches.
Bananas must be very ripe for best bread.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well to blend.
Bake in buttered casserole dish at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: energy chews
directions: Melt the butter and add the next 5 ingredients.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat and add the rolled oats, nuts and vanilla. Blend well.
Drop onto oiled cookie sheet or waxed paper.
Let cool and eat.

title: chocolate anise bars
directions: Mix butter/margarine, eggs, sugar and anise extract.
Add flour, baking powder, chopped walnuts and chocolate chips to first mixture.
Grease and flour pans (cookie sheets).
Form dough on cookie sheets like loaves.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: hobo steaks(best for camping; serves four)
directions: Roll hamburger meat into approximately one-inch balls.
Wash potatoes (do not peel) and cut into approximately one-inch squares. Scrape and cut carrots into about 1/2-inch lengths.
Separate cauliflower into bite sized pieces.
Peel onions and cut into 1/2-inch wedges.
Separate main ingredients into four equal portions and place each portion on a large piece of tinfoil.
Add one tablespoon of butter.
Season to taste with onion salt, garlic salt and black pepper.
Wrap portions in the tinfoil, folding edges to ensure a good seal.
Wrap and seal with a second layer of tinfoil.
Place in campfire coals.
Cover package with coals.
Cook 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from coals with extreme care as the tinfoil will have lost much of its strength and will have hot liquids inside.
Also open with care due to steam.
If opened with care, meals may be eaten directly from the "tinfoil plate".
Saves washing dishes later.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn and margarine with a spoon.
Stir in sour cream and eggs.
Add muffin mix.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand until consistency of dough.
Roll into small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Press into hard plastic candy molds (not rubber molds).
These mints are sticky and should be sugar coated before molding.
Pillow mints can also be made by rolling in long "snakes" and cutting apart with scissors or knife.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Bake pie crust slightly before pouring in mixture.
Mix all above ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour mixture into slighlty baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: clam fritters
directions: Mix and sift flour, salt and pepper.
Add clam liquor, milk and eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Add clams and butter.
Mix until well blended.
Drop from spoon into oil (375°) for 4 to 6 minutes until brown.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream the margarine; add sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and sour cream; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda; mix well.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients (rhubarb, flour, eggs, sugar and salt). When thoroughly blended, pour into unbaked shell. Blend brown sugar, flour and butter for topping. May have to add more flour to get the desired consistency. Sprinkle over rhubarb mix. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes. Enjoy!

title: pancakes or waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a bowl.
In separate bowl, mix egg, milk and oil.
Then add dry ingredients.
Do not overmix.
(The batter should look like heavy cream.)
Drop batter onto skillet that has been oiled.
Flip pancakes when bubbles appear on top. Serve plain or with butter or your favorite syrup.
Feeds 4.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Do not overbake. Remove cookies from pan and cool on wire racks.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour large cookie sheet. In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Beating at high speed, sprinkle in sugar 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition, until sugar is completely dissolved.
Beat in vanilla (whites should stand in stiff glossy peaks).
With rubber spatula fold in coconut and flour.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Saute diced chuck steak and garlic (dredged in flour) in oil. Drain and cook in a crock-pot or slow cooker along with V-8 juice for 3 to 4 hours.
Add vegetables and cook until done.
Add last 4 or 5 cups of water.
Serves 7.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in saucepan.
Mix 1/3 cup evaporated milk, 1 stick melted butter and cake mix.
Put 1/2 of the batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread a layer of chocolate chips, then pour the caramels over the top and spread it out. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Put the rest of the batter in and spread around.
Continue to bake for another 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook and peel sweet potatoes.
Mash and add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Put marshmallows on top the last 5 minutes.
Bake in casserole or souffle dish.

title: countryside chicken bake
directions: Line casserole with smoked beef or ham (thin sliced).
Put in breasts of chicken wrapped in bacon and cover with 1/2 pint sour cream and a can of mushroom soup (undiluted).
Bake, covered, for 3 hours at 300°.
(Have chicken breasts deboned and remove skin.) Simply delicious!

title: chicken fettucini
directions: Melt butter and add onions and green peppers; saute.
Add soup and stir until smooth; add cheese, a little at a time and let melt.
Add broth, pimento and chicken.
Simmer on low while cooking 3/4 pound fettucini.
Pour fettucini into 9 x 13-inch oblong pan; pour chicken sauce over it.
(Save some extra sauce to be served over baked fettucini.)
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Extra can be frozen.

title: herman kuchen
directions: Stir every day.
Keep in refrigerator.
Feed again on fifth day.
Bake on tenth day.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets. Mix sugar and cornstarch. Add vinegar. Let sauce boil for 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add butter. Pour sauce over beets. Let stand to absorb the sweet and sour flavor of sauce.

title: easy cocoa cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8-inch square or 9-inch round baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add the water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Beat with spoon or wire whisk until batter is smooth and well blended.

title: chicken and potato casserole
directions: Place thinly sliced
potatoes
in greased square baking pan. Top with chicken
and
onion.
Combine soup and milk and pour in baking pan.
Cover
and
bake
at 375° for 45 minutes. Remove cover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-orange salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and vinegar, then toss with remaining ingredients.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda and cocoa.
Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Add boiling water (mix will be runny). Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deviled potato salad
directions: Cut eggs in half; remove yolks.
Mash and blend with vinegar and mustard.
Add mayonnaise, sour cream, celery salt and salt. Mix well.
Chop egg whites.
Combine egg whites with potatoes and onion.
Fold in yolk mixture.
Chill.
Garnish with tomato wedges and cucumber slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix all together; form into small balls.
Cook until brown. Add 1 large jar spaghetti sauce with mushrooms and simmer 30 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Remove stem ends from tomatoes.
Slice in 1/2-inch slices. Combine flour, salt, pepper and basil or oregano.
Coat tomato slices with flour mixture.
Saute quickly in hot shortening until brown on one side, then turn.
Reduce heat.
Cook until soft. Remove to platter.
Serve immediately.

title: vitamin formula
directions: For hip dysplasia or arthritis, give two times daily to start, 2 weeks (selenium once daily only) thereafter once daily.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix with mixer.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll in finely chopped walnuts or parsley.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Soften cheeses by letting them set out overnight.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in tightly covered container. For each serving, use 1 heaping teaspoonful per cup of boiling water and stir until dissolved.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine in order given.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 55 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: peanut butter and fudge crunch bars
directions: Combine peanut butter morsels, corn syrup and 2 tablespoons butter in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Cook over hot water until morsels melt; stir well.
Add cereal, and stir well.
Press half of the mixture into a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, and chill while preparing chocolate layer. Set remaining cereal mixture aside.

title: rice croquettes
directions: Grate cheese and mix well into cooked rice.
Shape into croquettes.
Roll in
beaten
egg
and then in cracker crumbs. Fry in shallow cooking fat until brown as you like.

title: eggnog cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggnog, nutmeg and soda.
Mix well.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Chill.
Roll out on lightly floured surface and cut with cookie cutter or knife.
Brush with slightly beaten egg white and decorate with candied fruits or colored sugar, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately brown.

title: good and easy jello salad
directions: Mix together; ready to serve in 5 minutes.
Add chopped nuts and coconut if desired or add 1 cup of marshmallows.

title: chocolate citrus cooler
directions: In blender container, place milk, orange juice concentrate, syrup and 1 scoop ice cream.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses over ice or top with additional ice cream, if desired.
Makes about 3 (8 ounce) servings.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Dry washed lettuce leaves with paper towel.
Place in a large salad bowl.
Fry bacon and remove from fat.
To bacon fat in skillet stir in onion, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Cook 2 minutes.
Pour hot dressing over lettuce.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Toss to coat lettuce leaves evenly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Slice cabbage.
Add sesame seed, almonds, chicken, green onions and Top Ramen noodles (broken up).
Mix together sugar, pepper, salt, vinegar, oil and seasoning.
Put in salad and toss.

title: quick, rich, moist coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Have all ingredients to about 75 degrees.
Sift flour, sugar, powder and salt together.
Cut in the butter.
Break egg into a measuring cup.
Fill with milk. Beat and add to the dry ingredients with the vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased pan and over with honey bee glaze.
Bake about 25 minutes.

title: scrambled eggs with peppers and zucchini
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet.
Add peppers, zucchini, garlic and marjoram or oregano (if using dried herbs).
Saute 4 to 5 minutes until peppers begin to soften.
Pour off any liquid in skillet. Beat eggs with marjoram or oregano (if using fresh herbs) until fluffy.
Pour into skillet.
Swirl eggs around skillet with wooden spoon, cooking over medium heat until eggs are barely set.
Remove from heat and season with salt and pepper.
(Eggs will continue to cook in the pan.)
Serve immediately.

title: aggression cookies
directions: If you feel like throwing bricks or snarling at Santa, you can knead, mash, squeeze and beat the bejunior out of the dough.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except soda and popcorn in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart dish. Bring to a boil, then cook on full power for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in soda.
Put popped corn in brown grocery bag.
Pour syrup over corn. Close bag and shake. Cook in bag on High in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes. Shake and cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
May need more time.

title: crab dip
directions: In small bowl, beat together the cream cheese, mayonnaise, milk, garlic powder and hot pepper sauce.
Stir in crab meat and sprinkle with snipped chives.
Chill.
Serve with assorted vegetables.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute squash and onion in skillet on stove in olive oil on medium heat.
When tender (as desired) salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Cover and turn eye off and let cheese melt.
Delicious!!

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Remove all the water and pat dry with paper towels.
Crumble the spinach.
Add finely diced water chestnuts, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add finely chopped onion and soup mix.
Mix well.
Put mixture into a covered dish and let stand for 8 hours in refrigerator or longer.
Serve with crackers or vegetable sticks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop onion and saute in 1 1/2 tablespoons of butter.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Spray a
1 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add buttered bread crumbs or crushed potato chips on top during the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: kalua turkey
directions: Rinse, drain and dry turkey.
Line a large roasting pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Place the ti leaves, radiating from the center.
Place a banana leaf on the ti leaves.
Place the turkey on top of the leaves.
Rub the turkey with salt and liquid smoke on the inside and outside.
Fold the leaves around the turkey. Place the other banana leaf over the ti leaves.
Seal well with foil.
Roast in 350° oven for 4 hours, then lower to 325° for 1 to 2 hours.
Shred to serve.

title: grammy's spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat until smooth. Combine all dry ingredients, then alternately add buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in greased pans.
Tastes great with peanut butter frosting!

title: spicy chicken and pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a Dutch oven, over medium-high heat, cook and stir chicken in oil until chicken is lightly browned. Stir in pasta sauce, cream and basil.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in rigatoni and Parmesan cheese.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cover; bake 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Top with parsley and additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites first and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Add flour, milk, soda, vanilla and coconut, then add egg whites.
Put in 3 (9-inch) round pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry sour cream mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add strawberries, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let chill for 1 hour, spread on sour cream.
Spoon on remaining gelatin mixture on top of sour cream and chill.

title: micro fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in large microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High 2 minutes.
Mix well and pour into wax paper lined loaf pan and cool in refrigerator.

title: sweet and saucy apricot ribs
directions: Rub garlic into meaty side or ribs. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and place in a single layer in a large shallow baking dish. Pour 1 cup water into a pan and cover tightly with a lid or foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken with rosemary
directions: * For a more elegant dinner, use just chicken thighs.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, salt and milk.
Pour mixture over hot butter.
Pour peaches and juice over mixture.
Do not stir. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: lemon marinated sirloin steak
directions: Score fat edges of steak. Place meat in a shallow baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over steaks. Cover; let stand 4 hours in the refrigerator or over night, turning steaks several times. Remove steaks from marinade, reserving marinade. Pat excess moisture from steak with paper towels. Grill steak over medium-hot coals for 17 to 20 minutes. Turn, cook for 15 to 17 minutes more for medium-rare. Heat reserved marinade on grill.

title: halibut royal
directions: In a 10 x 6-inch baking dish, combine lemon juice, salt and paprika.
Add halibut steaks and marinate 15 minutes.
Turn steaks after 10 minutes. Cook onion in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Place onion on top of halibut and top with 6 green pepper strips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: carol's bean soup
directions: Soak all beans in bowl overnight, except lima beans.
Soak them separately. Cover sausage and ham hocks with water.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrot, celery and parsley.
Reduce heat to simmer. Simmer 1 hour.
Remove sausage after 15 minutes and set aside.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil and drain carrots, put in a 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Melt margarine and Velveeta together and pour over carrots.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Delicious.

title: auntie annie's pumpkin pie
directions: Blend together and pour into your favorite crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello fruit filling salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water.
Add the crushed pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Mix and add nut meats.
Pour into mold and chill.
Top with sweetened whipped cream or other desired topping.
Makes 12 large servings.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine.
When onions are clear, add flour and mix.
Add Cheez Whiz, half and half and crawfish to vegetables; mix well and simmer for 30 minutes.
Boil noodles as directed; drain.
Combine noodles and crawfish mixture.
Place in casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies into crumbs and reserve 1/4 cup for top.
Melt margarine and mix crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar; mix well.
Fold in half of the Cool Whip and spread over crumbs.
Prepare pudding with milk. Spread over mixture and chill.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill 8 hours or overnight. Makes 16 servings.
Preparation time:
30 minutes.

title: little sandwiches diane
directions: Cream together margarine, onion, mustard and poppy seed. Spread mixture on both halves of each bun.
Place a slice of ham, slice of cheese, then another slice of ham again, all trimmed to fit.
Cover with bun top.
(You can make up to 2 weeks ahead and freeze in foil.)
Heat for 15 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine 1 stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat together eggs, confectioners sugar and 2 sticks margarine no less than 15 minutes.
Spread over crumb crust.
Slice bananas over egg and confectioners sugar mixture. Spread the well-drained pineapple over the bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
May garnish with nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: country taters
directions: Wash potatoes; quarter lengthwise.
Cut each quarter in half. Mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Wet potatoes and coat in flour mixture.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place potatoes in butter and bake for 1 hour.

title: jo ann's deer jerky
directions: Marinate overnight.
Place in dehydrator for about 8 hours or bake in oven at 325° for 8 to 12 hours.

title: fried mashed potato patties
directions: Mash cold potatoes until soft; add milk; mix well.
Add egg, salt, pepper and flour.
Mix until well blended.
Fry in oil until golden brown on both sides.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Dump all together.
Combine and beat well.
Bake and let cool.

title: stove top rice pudding
directions: In heavy pot, combine first three ingredients.
Cook until rice is soft and starts to thicken.
In separate bowl, combine remaining three ingredients.
Add to thickened mixture and let simmer, stirring occasionally, until pudding reaches desired consistency.
Cool and serve.

title: air cookies
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Gradually add brown sugar and vanilla; continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in pecan halves.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and leave in oven an additional half hour.
Remove and cool.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: eggplant pie
directions: Saute peppers and onion in butter until tender.
Blend in spaghetti sauce and salt.
Bring to a boil and add eggplant.
Cook partially covered for 10 minutes or until eggplant is almost tender.
Pour 1/2 the mixture into the pie shell.
Top with 1/2 the cheese.
Add remaining mixture and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Place in a small pan the peel from an orange and a lemon.
Add 2 or 3 cinnamon sticks and 1 or 2 tablespoons whole cloves.
Pour about 2 cups of water over the fruit and spices and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat until the liquid is at a low boil.

title: deer
directions: This recipe takes approximately 12 1/2 to 16 1/2 hours to prepare.
Soak deer hindquarter in vinegar and salt water for about 4 hours.
Place meat in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

Combine all other ingredients together; pour part of marinade over meat and soak for about 2 hours, rotating meat about every 30 minutes. Cover with foil; place on grill and cook very slowly, turning meat every hour or so, until meat is tender and comes off the bone easily.
This takes between 6 to 10 hours.
Remove from grill, tear meat into small pieces and put back in baking dish.
Add remaining marinade to meat; return to grill and heat for 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Run cold water over linguini to cool.
Add tomatoes and cucumbers.
Add seasoning and bottle of dressing.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken wild rice
directions: Place 2 types of rice in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soup and water over rice mixture.
Dip cut up chicken in melted margarine.
Place on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle seasoning from Uncle Ben's rice.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Uncover; sprinkle almonds and bake 30 minutes more.

title: curried vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with raw vegetables. If thinned with a bit of milk, this also makes a good salad dressing.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar until blended.
Cool.
Stir in one egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla and nuts. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut brownies while still warm.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for about 3 hours or until it is cold. Cut bread in triangles and toast well.

title: mrs. cook's salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Soften butter; add sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sprinkle the fruits and nuts with 1 cup of flour; set aside.
Add baking powder and salt to the remaining 3 cups of flour; sift together.
Gradually add flour mixture to batter.
Mix in cherries, raisins and nuts.
Add lemon extract.
Bake in a tube pan for 2 hours at 300°, then 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Treat as a fruit cake, but do not pour liquor on it.
Do not ice cake.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In saucepan, boil chicken breasts until tender.
In chicken broth, cook spaghetti.
In skillet, melt margarine and saute bell pepper and onion.
Add skillet mixture to chicken (chopped) and drained spaghetti.
Then add cream of chicken soup and tomatoes. Add cheese and stir until cheese melts.

title: marvelous salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine tomatoes, greens, croutons and chopped onions.
Add turkey, cheese and dressing; toss lightly.

title: wienie ladas
directions: Cook tortillas in water according to directions on package. Combine the next 3 ingredients.
Place frankfurters on each tortilla; top with 2 tablespoons chili mixture (reserve remaining).
Roll tortillas around frankfurters; arrange in pan, seam side down.
Combine remaining chili mixture and tomato sauce; pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle with chili pepper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: impossible zucchini tomato pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°; grease 10-inch deep dish pie pan.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour in pan over other ingredients. Bake until knife comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: chuckwagon stew
directions: Dust beef with flour.
Thoroughly brown on all sides in hot oil, turning often.
Add salt, chili powder, pepper, thyme, bay leaf, tomatoes, green pepper, beef stock and water.
Cover and simmer over low heat until meat is almost tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally to prevent foods from sticking.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and celery.
Cover and cook 30 minutes. Add peas; cook until vegetables are done, about 15 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: grits casserole
directions: Stir grits into salted boiling water.
Cook until thick; remove from heat and stir in butter, garlic, Tabasco sauce, grated cheese, salt and paprika. Add mixture of 2 eggs in a cup with milk to make one cup.
Beat well before adding to grit mixture.
Bake in greased casserole at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple pie without apples
directions: Break each cracker into 4 pieces.
Mix water, sugar, cream of tartar and cinnamon.
Stir in crackers.
Bake at 450° for 35 minutes.

title: raspberry meatball surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients except half and half; add when all else is mixed.
Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove; add sauce and jelly and simmer for 1 hour.

title: skillet fried corn
directions: Heat
butter in skillet until hot. Add corn, ham, onion and green
pepper.
Saute,
stirring
often,
until onion and pepper are
crisp and tender (about 5 minutes). Stir in salt, pepper
and milk. Cut down heat. Let warm just long enough to heat thoroughly.

title: fluffy rice and chicken(serves 4)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix mushroom soup and milk; reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture.
Mix rest of soup, rice, mushrooms (with liquid) and 1/2 envelope of onion soup.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool while mixing vegetables in separate bowl.
Once mixture is cool, pour over vegetables.
Will store up to 3 weeks in sealed container in refrigerator.

title: angel hair tomato basil toss
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil. Add garlic and green onions. Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper. Cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently.

Prepare angel hair according to package directions. Drain. Toss tomato mixture with hot cooked angel hair. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Refrigerate leftovers. Recipe can be doubled using no more than 1/2 cup oil.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together in 10-inch baking dish.
Cover with bacon in sizes you desire.
Bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until it thickens.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Soften ice cream and sherbet and mix.
Pour ginger ale over mixture.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Sprinkle zucchini with salt and pepper.
Dip into egg and dredge in corn meal.
Fry zucchini in hot vegetable oil over medium heat until golden brown, turning once.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In bowl beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in remaining ingredients except tomatoes and parsley until well blended.
Turn into 1-quart greased casserole.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Garnish with tomatoes and parsley.

title: oriental pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in Crisco.
Place on tray in pressure cooker. Add 2 tablespoons rice on each pork chop.

title: a nice useful cake(very old recipe)
directions: Beat the butter to a cream; beat the eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients together; then add the butter, milk and eggs.
Beat the mixture well for a few minutes.
Put the batter in a greased cake pan and bake it at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.
The raisins and almonds could be omitted and flavoring used instead.

title: stroganoff beef burgers
directions: Brown ground beef and bacon.
Add onion.
Cook until tender (onion) but not brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Blend flour and other seasonings into meat mixture.
Stir in soup.
Cook slowly (low), uncovered 20 minutes.
Stirring frequently.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine all together; beat 4 minutes on medium speed.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 55 minutes; do not underbake.
Cook 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: fresh fruit dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender in order listed.
Can be kept in refrigerator for approximately 2 weeks.
If too thick, add small amount of milk.

title: chicken paprika
directions: In 5-quart pan, saute diced onion in butter until transparent. Add tomato juice, water, paprika, sugar, salt, pepper and chicken.
Boil over medium heat for 45 minutes.
Remove chicken and thicken gravy with flour and water.
Slowly add heavy cream. Place chicken back in and reheat.
Serve over elbow macaroni.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt the caramels in a double boiler over hot water.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Drizzle each cluster with 1/2 teaspoon chocolate.
Chill 5 to 10 minutes, or until the chocolate is set.
Makes 24 pieces.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix and let stand covered in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Add enough milk to fill freezer.

title: creamed potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted boiling water until tender.
Cool. Peel and dice.
Sprinkle with salt and mixture of vinegar and water.

title: chili
directions: Brown the meat until pink is gone.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for 2 or 3 hours.
This chili does not give people the usual indigestion!

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, molasses, vinegar and remaining dry ingredients all together.
Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Place far apart on cookie sheet to allow for spreading.
Bake in moderate oven (350°).
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: great casserole
directions: In greased casserole place ham slices.
Cover with broccoli. Place chicken breast on top and pour cream of chicken soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until chicken is done.
May be served with mashed potatoes or alone.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice and whipped topping.
Beat on medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Pour into lightly greased mold or serving container and freeze for about two hours or until set.

title: favorite diet punch
directions: Note:
We usually freeze an orange juice ring to add just before serving.
This is the punch we serve at most of our church functions.

title: peach delight
directions: Bake cake by directions on box in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding, milk and sour cream and refrigerate.

title: fruit drink
directions: Mix ingredients in a pitcher.
Chill until ready to serve. Great if served with crushed ice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and slice berries.
Place the strawberries in the pie shell; spread glaze over top.
Chill for about
5 to 10 minutes and then serve with Cool Whip.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Roll beef in flour.
Brown in hot fat in cooker.
Add enough water to reserved mushroom liquid to measure 3/4 cup.
Add mushrooms, mushroom-water mixture and remaining ingredients except sour cream to cooker.
Cover, set control on vent tube and cook 15 minutes after control jiggles.
Cool cooker normally for 5 minutes, then place under faucet.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve with noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Smash the avocados on large plate.
Layer sour cream and salsa. Put the grated cheese on and the tomato.
Refrigerate dip 1 hour. Serve with tortilla chips.
